container registry."},{"heading":"16. Edge & IoT Services","content":"Use CloudFront, Lambda@Edge, AWS IoT Core and Greengrass."},{"heading":"17. Disaster Recovery & Backups","content":"Use cross-region replication, snapshots, Backup service."},{"heading":"18. Governance & Tagging","content":"Enforce resource tagging, AWS Organizations, Service Control Policies."},{"heading":"19. DevOps & Automation","content":"- Use AWS CDK, CloudFormation macros, automated updates and drift detection"},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Follow Well-Architected Framework\n- Use multi-AZ / multi-region\n- Principle of least privilege\n- Monitor and audit continuously"}],"related":["bitbucket-roadmap","webrtc-roadmap","springboot-roadmap","metamask-roadmap","huggingface-roadmap"]},{"slug":"azure-roadmap","title":"Azure Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Microsoft Azure in 2025 with this comprehensive roadmap covering core services, networking, security, DevOps, and cloud-native best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Azure?","content":"Microsoft Azure is a cloud computing platform offering a broad range of services including compute, storage, database, networking, and AI—integrated for enterprise-grade reliability and hybrid-cloud capabilities.","links":[{"text":"Azure Documentation","href":"https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/"}]},{"heading":"Why Azure?","content":"Azure combines enterprise integration, hybrid-cloud support, compliance, and security, making it ideal for large organizations, Windows-centric environments, and global-scale deployments."},{"heading":"1. Identity & Access Management","content":"Use Azure Active Directory (AAD), roles, RBAC, and multi‑factor authentication (MFA)."},{"heading":"2. Compute Services","content":"Use Azure Virtual Machines, Azure App Service, Azure Functions (serverless), and Azure Container Instances."},{"heading":"3. Networking & Connectivity","content":"Set up Virtual Network (VNet), subnets, NSGs, Azure Firewall, VPN Gateway, and Azure ExpressRoute."},{"heading":"4. Storage & Databases","content":"Use Azure Storage (Blob, File, Queue, Table), Azure SQL Database, Cosmos DB, and managed SQL servers."},{"heading":"5. Serverless & Event-Driven Architecture","content":"Use Azure Functions, Event Grid, Service Bus, and Logic Apps."},{"heading":"6. Infrastructure as Code","content":"Use ARM Templates, Bicep, or Terraform to define and deploy resources declaratively."},{"heading":"7. CI/CD & DevOps","content":"Use Azure DevOps / GitHub Actions, Azure Repos, Pipelines, Artifacts, and Boards."},{"heading":"8. Monitoring & Logging","content":"Use Azure Monitor, Log Analytics, Application Insights, and set up alerts and dashboards."},{"heading":"9. Security & Compliance","content":"Use Azure Key Vault, Azure Policy, Azure Security Center, Defender for Cloud, and Azure Sentinel."},{"heading":"10. Kubernetes & Containers","content":"Use Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), ACR, and Azure Container Apps."},{"heading":"11. AI & Analytics","content":"Use Azure Cognitive Services, Synapse Analytics, Databricks, and HDInsight."},{"heading":"12. Networking Patterns & CDN","content":"Use Azure Front Door, CDN, Traffic Manager, and load balancing."},{"heading":"13. Cost Management & Governance","content":"Use Cost Management, Azure Advisor, Management Groups, and tagging strategy."},{"heading":"14. Disaster Recovery & Backup","content":"Use Azure Backup, Site Recovery, and geo-redundancy."},{"heading":"15. Identity Federation & Hybrid-cloud","content":"Use Azure AD Connect, Hybrid identities, and Azure Arc."},{"heading":"16. Performance Tuning & Scaling","content":"Auto-scale VMs, configure throughput for storage and Cosmos DB."},{"heading":"17. Edge & IoT Services","content":"Use Azure IoT Hub, IoT Edge, Azure Sphere, and Azure Stack Edge."},{"heading":"18. Compliance Certifications","content":"Leverage Azure’s compliance with GDPR, HIPAA, ISO, FedRAMP, and more."},{"heading":"19. Best Practices","content":"- Design for resilience and high-availability\n- Use least-privilege IAM\n- Automate deployments\n- Monitor performance, cost & security"}],"related":["google-cloud-roadmap","vue-roadmap","svelte-roadmap","nodejs-roadmap","ios-roadmap"]},{"slug":"google-cloud-roadmap","title":"Google Cloud Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Google Cloud Platform (GCP) in 2025 with this roadmap covering core compute, storage, networking, AI/ML, DevOps, and cloud-native best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Google Cloud?","content":"Google Cloud Platform is a suite of cloud services including compute, storage, databases, AI/ML, and analytics, offering global infrastructure and data-driven innovation.","links":[{"text":"GCP Documentation","href":"https://cloud.google.com/docs"}]},{"heading":"Why Google Cloud?","content":"GCP excels in AI/ML, global networking, data analytics, Kubernetes (GKE), and developer-first APIs—with deep integration into open-source and data-driven tools."},{"heading":"1. IAM & Security","content":"Use Cloud IAM, Service Accounts, VPC Service Controls, and Binary Authorization."},{"heading":"2. Compute Options","content":"Use Compute Engine (VMs), Google Kubernetes Engine, and Cloud Functions / Run (serverless)."},{"heading":"3. Storage & Database Services","content":"Use Cloud Storage, Filestore, Spanner, Cloud SQL, Firestore, and Bigtable."},{"heading":"4. Networking & CDN","content":"Configure VPC, Cloud Load Balancing, Cloud CDN, Interconnect, and Cloud Router."},{"heading":"5. Serverless & Event-driven Architecture","content":"Use Cloud Functions, Eventarc, Pub/Sub, and Workflows."},{"heading":"6. Infrastructure as Code","content":"Use Deployment Manager, Terraform, or Pulumi to manage infrastructure declaratively."},{"heading":"7. CI/CD & DevOps","content":"Use Cloud Build, Cloud Source Repositories, Artifact Registry, Cloud Deploy, and GitHub/GitLab integrations."},{"heading":"8. Monitoring & Logging","content":"Use Cloud Monitoring, Logging, Trace, and Ops Agent with dashboards and alerts."},{"heading":"9. Security & Compliance","content":"Use Cloud Armor, Security Command Center, KMS, Secret Manager, and VPC Service Controls."},{"heading":"10. Containers & Kubernetes","content":"Use GKE, Anthos, and Container Registry for hybrid-cloud consistency."},{"heading":"11. AI & Machine Learning","content":"Use AI Platform, Vertex AI, BigQuery ML, Vision, Speech-to-Text, and AutoML."},{"heading":"12. Data Analytics & Warehousing","content":"Use BigQuery, Cloud Dataflow, Dataproc, and Pub/Sub for event streaming."},{"heading":"13. Edge & IoT Services","content":"Use IoT Core, Edge TPU, and distributed edge computing."},{"heading":"14. Disaster Recovery & Backup","content":"Use snapshots, geo-redundant storage, and replication strategies."},{"heading":"15. Cost Management & Optimization","content":"Use Cloud Billing, Recommender, and commit plans to save costs."},{"heading":"16. Identity & Hybrid-cloud","content":"Use Identity-Aware Proxy, Workload Identity, and Anthos for hybrid deployments."},{"heading":"17. Governance & Policy","content":"Use Organization Policies, Resource Manager, and Tagging for structure."},{"heading":"18. Compliance & Certifications","content":"Leverage compliance with PCI, HIPAA, ISO, FedRAMP, and more."},{"heading":"19. Best Practices","content":"- Design for auto-scaling and global availability\n- Use least-privilege IAM\n- Automate deployments and monitoring\n- Evaluate networking across regions"}],"related":["typescript-roadmap","cpp-roadmap","rust-roadmap","prometheus-roadmap","git-roadmap"]},{"slug":"linux-roadmap","title":"Linux Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Linux system administration and usage in 2025 with this roadmap covering core commands, shell scripting, services, networking, security, containers, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Linux?","content":"Linux is a family of open-source Unix-like operating systems running the Linux kernel, widely used for servers, desktops, embedded systems, and development environments.","links":[{"text":"Linux Kernel Archives","href":"https://www.kernel.org/"}]},{"heading":"Why Linux?","content":"Linux is powerful, stable, secure, open-source, and highly customizable—making it the foundation of servers, cloud infrastructure, and developer environments."},{"heading":"1. Command Line Basics","content":"Learn file navigation, text manipulation, permissions, pipelines, and shell basics.","code":"ls -lah /etc\ncd /var/log\ngrep -R \"error\" *.log | less"},{"heading":"2. Users, Groups & Permissions","content":"Manage user/group accounts, file ownership, and permissions using chmod, chown, and sudo.","code":"sudo useradd alice\necho \"password\" | passwd alice\nchmod 750 /srv/data"},{"heading":"3. Shell Scripting","content":"Write bash scripts to automate tasks, use conditionals and loops.","code":"#!/bin/bash\nfor file in /var/log/*.log; do\necho \"Processing $file\"\ndone"},{"heading":"4. Package Management","content":"Use distro package managers (apt, yum, pacman), install, update, and remove software.","code":"sudo apt update && sudo apt install nginx"},{"heading":"5. Systemd & Service Management","content":"Use systemctl to manage system and service units.","code":"sudo systemctl start nginx\nsudo systemctl enable nginx"},{"heading":"6. Networking & Firewalls","content":"Configure network interfaces, services like ssh, iptables, nftables.","code":"ip addr show eth0\nsudo ufw allow 22\ntcpdump -i eth0"},{"heading":"7. Logs & Monitoring","content":"Use journalctl, logrotate, monitoring tools like top, htop, Nagios, or Prometheus exporters.","code":"journalctl -u nginx\nwatch -n 5 df -h"},{"heading":"8. Storage & Filesystems","content":"Mount/unmount filesystems, understand ext4/XFS, LVM, RAID.","code":"sudo pvcreate /dev/sdb\nsudo vgcreate data_vg /dev/sdb\nsudo lvcreate -L 10G -n data_lv data_vg"},{"heading":"9. Backup & Recovery","content":"Use tools like rsync, tar, cron jobs, and backups across networks.","code":"rsync -avz /etc/ backup:/backups/etc"},{"heading":"10. Userspace Process Management","content":"Manage processes, signals, cgroups, and jobs.","code":"ps aux | grep nginx\nkill -HUP 1234"},{"heading":"11. Virtualization & Containers","content":"Use KVM/libvirt, Docker, Podman to create and manage containers/VMs.","code":"docker run -d nginx\ndocker ps"},{"heading":"12. Security & Hardening","content":"Use SSH key auth, fail2ban, SELinux/AppArmor, and regular patching."},{"heading":"13. Network Services","content":"Deploy services like HTTP (Apache/nginx), SSH, DNS, DHCP."},{"heading":"14. Cron & Scheduling","content":"Use cron, at, and systemd timers to schedule recurring tasks."},{"heading":"15. Monitoring & Alerting","content":"Use Prometheus/node_exporter, Grafana, and alertmanager."},{"heading":"16. Kernel & Build Tools","content":"Compile custom kernels, use build tools like gcc, make."},{"heading":"17. Troubleshooting & Debugging","content":"Use strace, lsof, dmesg, perf, tcpdump, and debug live services."},{"heading":"18. Configuration Management","content":"Use Ansible, Puppet, Chef to manage fleets of servers."},{"heading":"19. Cloud & DevOps Integration","content":"Run Linux on cloud VMs, integrate with CI pipelines and infrastructure-as-code."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Automate tasks\n- Keep minimal installs\n- Monitor health and logs\n- Harden systems and keep backups"}],"related":["opencv-roadmap","tensorflow-roadmap","grafana-roadmap","mocha-roadmap","swift-roadmap"]},{"slug":"ubuntu-roadmap","title":"Ubuntu Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Ubuntu in 2025, from desktop usage to server management, software repositories, system services, snaps, containers, and enterprise best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Ubuntu?","content":"Ubuntu is a Debian-based Linux distribution maintained by Canonical. Known for its user-friendliness, it is widely used across desktops, servers, IoT, and cloud platforms.","links":[{"text":"Official Ubuntu Site","href":"https://ubuntu.com"}]},{"heading":"Why Ubuntu?","content":"Ubuntu provides long-term support (LTS) releases, strong community backing, and built-in tools for developers and DevOps engineers. It supports cloud-native workflows and snap-based applications out of the box."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Flavors","content":"Explore flavors like Ubuntu Desktop (GNOME), Ubuntu Server, Kubuntu, Xubuntu, and Ubuntu MATE. Use live USBs and ISO images to install.","code":"sudo dd if=ubuntu.iso of=/dev/sdX bs=4M status=progress && sync"},{"heading":"2. Desktop Environment & UI","content":"Customize GNOME Shell with themes, extensions, and workspaces. Use GNOME Tweaks for advanced settings.","links":[{"text":"Customize Ubuntu Desktop","href":"https://itsfoss.com/gnome-shell-extensions/"}]},{"heading":"3. APT & Package Sources","content":"Use `apt`, add PPAs, manage `.deb` packages, and understand sources.list configuration.","code":"sudo add-apt-repository ppa:graphics-drivers/ppa\nsudo apt update && sudo apt install nvidia-driver-535"},{"heading":"4. Snaps & Flatpak","content":"Snap packages are sandboxed and auto-updating. Flatpak offers an alternative app distribution system.","code":"sudo snap install postman\nflatpak install flathub org.mozilla.firefox"},{"heading":"5. System Services & Systemd","content":"Manage services and daemons with systemd. Replace older Upstart service manager.","code":"sudo systemctl start apache2\nsudo systemctl enable apache2\nsudo systemctl status apache2"},{"heading":"6. UFW Firewall","content":"Ubuntu uses UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall) as a frontend to iptables. It simplifies firewall configuration.","code":"sudo ufw enable\nsudo ufw allow 'Nginx Full'\nsudo ufw status verbose"},{"heading":"7. Network Configuration","content":"Modern Ubuntu uses Netplan for YAML-based network configs. Useful for cloud and static IPs.","code":"sudo nano /etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml\nsudo netplan apply"},{"heading":"8. LXD Containers","content":"LXD is a next-gen system container manager ideal for isolated service environments.","code":"sudo snap install lxd\nlxd init\nlxc launch ubuntu:22.04 my-container"},{"heading":"9. Cloud & Juju","content":"Juju allows model-driven deployment across AWS, GCP, Azure, and local LXD setups.","links":[{"text":"Getting Started with Juju","href":"https://juju.is/docs"}]},{"heading":"10. Ubuntu Server Roles","content":"Set up Ubuntu as web, database, DNS, mail, file server using LAMP, Samba, or BIND9.","code":"sudo apt install apache2 mysql-server php libapache2-mod-php"},{"heading":"11. Backup & Snapshots","content":"Use tools like `rsync`, Timeshift, or create LVM/ZFS snapshots for regular backups.","code":"rsync -aAXv /home /mnt/backup/home_backup\nsudo timeshift --create --comments 'Daily Backup'"},{"heading":"12. Security & AppArmor","content":"Use AppArmor for mandatory access control, enable automatic security updates, and fail2ban for SSH brute-force protection.","code":"sudo apt install fail2ban\nsudo ufw limit ssh\nsudo apparmor_status"},{"heading":"13. Snap & Deb Packaging","content":"Package applications using Snapcraft or build `.deb` files for apt distribution.","links":[{"text":"Snapcraft Docs","href":"https://snapcraft.io/docs"}]},{"heading":"14. Kernel Updates & HWE","content":"Ubuntu offers Hardware Enablement (HWE) kernels to support newer hardware on LTS versions.","code":"sudo apt install --install-recommends linux-generic-hwe-22.04"},{"heading":"15. Performance & Logs","content":"Use tools like `htop`, `iotop`, `systemd-analyze`, and monitor logs in `/var/log`.","code":"htop\njournalctl -xe\nsystemd-analyze blame"},{"heading":"16. Community & Support","content":"Engage with the community via AskUbuntu, Launchpad, or Canonical’s Discourse forums.","links":[{"text":"Ask Ubuntu","href":"https://askubuntu.com/"},{"text":"Ubuntu Forums","href":"https://discourse.ubuntu.com/"}]},{"heading":"17. Enterprise & Security","content":"Use Ubuntu Pro for live patching, FIPS 140-2 security modules, and 10-year LTS support.","links":[{"text":"Ubuntu Pro (Canonical)","href":"https://ubuntu.com/pro"}]},{"heading":"18. LTS Maintenance","content":"Understand Ubuntu LTS lifecycle: 5 years standard support, 10 years with Ubuntu Pro. Regular kernel updates and backports are included.","links":[{"text":"Ubuntu Release Cycle","href":"https://ubuntu.com/about/release-cycle"}]},{"heading":"19. Virtualization & Cloud Images","content":"Ubuntu supports KVM, QEMU, and cloud-init preinstalled images. Spin up VMs or cloud instances easily.","code":"sudo apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system virt-manager"},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use LTS releases for production\n- Automate with Ansible or cloud-init\n- Isolate apps in Snap or LXD\n- Keep the system updated regularly\n- Use encrypted volumes with LUKS"}],"related":["rest-api-roadmap","algolia-roadmap","firebase-roadmap","supabase-roadmap","nextjs-roadmap"]},{"slug":"android-roadmap","title":"Android Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Android development in 2025 with this comprehensive roadmap covering Java/Kotlin, Android Studio, UI, Jetpack Compose, Firebase, testing, publishing, and more.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Android Development?","content":"Android development involves building applications for devices running the Android OS using Java, Kotlin, or frameworks like Flutter or React Native."},{"heading":"Why Android?","content":"Android powers over 70% of the mobile market, offering flexibility, massive reach, and strong support from Google. It’s ideal for startups and enterprise apps alike."},{"heading":"1. Learn Java or Kotlin","content":"Kotlin is now preferred for Android, though Java is still used. Learn OOP, functions, classes, and collections.","links":[{"text":"Kotlin Docs","href":"https://kotlinlang.org/docs/home.html"}],"code":"fun greet(name: String): String {\n  return \"Hello, $name\"\n}"},{"heading":"2. Set Up Android Studio","content":"Install Android Studio, configure the SDK Manager, and start using the emulator or real device for testing.","links":[{"text":"Download Android Studio","href":"https://developer.android.com/studio"}]},{"heading":"3. App Fundamentals","content":"Understand Activities, Fragments, Intents, Context, and the AndroidManifest.xml.","code":"val intent = Intent(this, SecondActivity::class.java)\nstartActivity(intent)"},{"heading":"4. UI Design with XML","content":"Design layouts with XML using Views, Layouts, Buttons, and ImageViews.","code":"<Button\n  android:id=\"@+id/btnClick\"\n  android:text=\"Click Me\" />"},{"heading":"5. Jetpack Compose (Modern UI)","content":"Learn declarative UI with Jetpack Compose for faster, reactive UIs.","links":[{"text":"Jetpack Compose Basics","href":"https://developer.android.com/jetpack/compose"}],"code":"@Composable\nfun Greeting(name: String) {\n  Text(\"Hello $name\")\n}"},{"heading":"6. MVVM Architecture","content":"Use ViewModel, LiveData, Repository pattern, and DataBinding for clean code separation."},{"heading":"7. Room Database","content":"Use Room for local data persistence with SQLite.","code":"@Entity data class User(@PrimaryKey val id: Int, val name: String)"},{"heading":"8. Networking (Retrofit/Volley)","content":"Fetch data from APIs using Retrofit or Volley.","code":"interface ApiService {\n  @GET(\"users\")\n  suspend fun getUsers(): List<User>\n}"},{"heading":"9. Firebase Integration","content":"Add Firebase Authentication, Firestore, Realtime DB, Push Notifications, and Analytics.","links":[{"text":"Firebase Docs","href":"https://firebase.google.com/docs/android/setup"}]},{"heading":"10. Dependency Injection (Hilt)","content":"Use Hilt for scalable dependency injection across app modules."},{"heading":"11. Permissions & Sensors","content":"Handle runtime permissions, sensors (like GPS, Camera), and AndroidX libraries."},{"heading":"12. Testing","content":"Unit test with JUnit, instrumented UI testing with Espresso, and use Mockito for mocks."},{"heading":"13. Jetpack Libraries","content":"Use Jetpack Navigation, Lifecycle, WorkManager, Paging3, DataStore, and CameraX."},{"heading":"14. Publish to Google Play","content":"Sign APKs, build release variants, and publish to the Play Console with assets and descriptions.","links":[{"text":"Publishing Guide","href":"https://developer.android.com/studio/publish"}]},{"heading":"15. Best Practices","content":"- Use Jetpack Compose\n- Avoid memory leaks\n- Follow Material Design\n- Use modular architecture"}],"related":["svelte-roadmap","tailwindcss-roadmap","postgresql-roadmap","pytorch-roadmap","huggingface-roadmap"]},{"slug":"ios-roadmap","title":"iOS Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master iOS development in 2025 with this comprehensive guide covering Swift, UIKit, SwiftUI, Core Data, API handling, unit testing, and App Store deployment.","sections":[{"heading":"What is iOS Development?","content":"iOS development focuses on building applications for iPhones, iPads, and Apple Watches using Swift and Apple’s frameworks like UIKit and SwiftUI."},{"heading":"Why iOS?","content":"iOS users spend more on apps, and Apple offers a refined ecosystem, consistent APIs, and strong market presence—ideal for premium apps and startups."},{"heading":"1. Learn Swift Programming","content":"Swift is Apple's modern language for iOS. Learn classes, structs, enums, closures, and optionals.","links":[{"text":"Swift Language Guide","href":"https://swift.org/documentation/"}],"code":"func greet(name: String) -> String {\n  return \"Hello, \\(name)\"\n}"},{"heading":"2. Set Up Xcode","content":"Install Xcode from the App Store, set up your Apple Developer account, and build sample projects."},{"heading":"3. UIKit vs SwiftUI","content":"UIKit is imperative; SwiftUI is declarative. Start with UIKit and then move to SwiftUI for modern apps.","code":"struct ContentView: View {\n  var body: some View {\n    Text(\"Hello, iOS!\")\n  }\n}"},{"heading":"4. ViewControllers & Storyboards","content":"Learn UIViewController, NavigationController, Segues, and AutoLayout using Interface Builder."},{"heading":"5. SwiftUI Fundamentals","content":"Build apps with Views, State, Bindings, Modifiers, and Combine framework for reactive programming.","links":[{"text":"SwiftUI Tutorials","href":"https://developer.apple.com/tutorials/swiftui"}]},{"heading":"6. MVVM Architecture","content":"Use ViewModel to separate logic and maintain clean SwiftUI apps. Combine helps with reactive state updates."},{"heading":"7. Core Data & Realm","content":"Persist data using Core Data or Realm. Use @FetchRequest in SwiftUI.","code":"@FetchRequest(entity: Item.entity(), sortDescriptors: []) var items: FetchedResults<Item>"},{"heading":"8. API Calls & JSON Decoding","content":"Use `URLSession` and `Codable` for network requests and parsing.","code":"struct User: Codable { let id: Int; let name: String }\nURLSession.shared.dataTask(with: url) {...}"},{"heading":"9. Combine & Async/Await","content":"Use Combine for reactive data streams, or Swift 5.5’s async/await for simpler code."},{"heading":"10. Push Notifications","content":"Set up APNs, use Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM), and handle foreground/background events."},{"heading":"11. App Permissions","content":"Request and handle permissions for camera, location, photos, and notifications via Info.plist."},{"heading":"12. Testing (Unit & UI)","content":"Write XCTest unit tests and UI tests. Use XCUITest for simulating user interaction."},{"heading":"13. In-App Purchases & Ads","content":"Use StoreKit for IAPs and integrate AdMob or Apple Ads for monetization."},{"heading":"14. App Store Submission","content":"Prepare assets, run archive builds, and submit via Transporter or Xcode to App Store Connect.","links":[{"text":"App Store Submission Guide","href":"https://developer.apple.com/app-store/submission/"}]},{"heading":"15. Best Practices","content":"- Use SwiftUI for new projects\n- Avoid force unwrapping (!)\n- Write unit tests\n- Follow HIG (Human Interface Guidelines)"}],"related":["aspnet-roadmap","cpp-roadmap","digitalocean-roadmap","strapi-roadmap","tailwindcss-roadmap"]},{"slug":"react-native-roadmap","title":"React Native Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master React Native in 2025 with this comprehensive roadmap covering components, navigation, state management, native modules, testing, performance, and publishing for Android and iOS.","sections":[{"heading":"What is React Native?","content":"React Native is a popular open-source framework by Meta for building cross-platform mobile apps using JavaScript and React. It allows developers to write native-feeling apps for both Android and iOS from a single codebase."},{"heading":"Why React Native?","content":"With React Native, you get faster development cycles, hot-reloading, access to a large ecosystem, and the ability to write platform-specific code when needed. Major companies like Instagram, Uber, and Shopify use it."},{"heading":"1. JavaScript & React Fundamentals","content":"Start by mastering ES6+ JavaScript and React concepts like JSX, props, state, hooks, and functional components.","links":[{"text":"JavaScript Info","href":"https://javascript.info/"},{"text":"React Docs","href":"https://reactjs.org/docs/getting-started.html"}],"code":"const Greet = ({ name }) => <Text>Hello, {name}!</Text>;"},{"heading":"2. Environment Setup","content":"Install Node.js, watchman, Android Studio (for Android), Xcode (for iOS), and set up React Native CLI or use Expo CLI for faster prototyping.","links":[{"text":"React Native CLI Setup","href":"https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup"},{"text":"Expo CLI Setup","href":"https://docs.expo.dev/"}]},{"heading":"3. Core Components","content":"Familiarize with Text, View, ScrollView, FlatList, Image, Button, TextInput, etc.","code":"<View><TextInput placeholder='Enter Name' /><Button title='Submit' /></View>"},{"heading":"4. Styling in React Native","content":"Use Flexbox, StyleSheet.create, and platform-specific styling. Consider Tailwind-like utilities with libraries like `nativewind`."},{"heading":"5. Navigation","content":"Use `react-navigation` for Stack, Tab, Drawer navigators.","links":[{"text":"React Navigation","href":"https://reactnavigation.org/"}],"code":"const Stack = createNativeStackNavigator();"},{"heading":"6. State Management","content":"Start with useState and useContext. Learn Redux, Zustand, or Recoil for complex state handling.","code":"const [count, setCount] = useState(0);"},{"heading":"7. API Calls & Async Storage","content":"Use `fetch` or Axios for REST APIs and `@react-native-async-storage/async-storage` for persistent local storage."},{"heading":"8. Platform APIs & Permissions","content":"Access camera, geolocation, notifications, and permissions using `react-native-permissions` and other APIs."},{"heading":"9. Native Modules & Linking","content":"Use `NativeModules`, create custom modules, or integrate with Swift/Java/Kotlin when needed."},{"heading":"10. Expo vs React Native CLI","content":"Use Expo for easier setup and libraries. Eject to React Native CLI for deeper customization."},{"heading":"11. Animations","content":"Use `Animated` API or `react-native-reanimated` and libraries like `moti` for smoother animations."},{"heading":"12. Testing","content":"Test components with Jest, React Native Testing Library, and use Detox for E2E testing."},{"heading":"13. Performance Optimization","content":"Use FlatList optimization, lazy loading, memoization, and `useCallback` to avoid unnecessary re-renders."},{"heading":"14. App Store / Play Store Publishing","content":"Configure release builds, icons, splash screens, and publish via App Store Connect & Google Play Console."},{"heading":"15. Best Practices","content":"- Follow folder structure\n- Avoid anonymous functions in render\n- Modularize business logic\n- Use TypeScript for better maintainability"}],"related":["docker-roadmap","algolia-roadmap","springboot-roadmap","php-roadmap","prisma-roadmap"]},{"slug":"flutter-roadmap","title":"Flutter Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Flutter in 2025 with this developer roadmap covering Dart, widgets, state management, animations, packages, testing, and deployment for cross-platform mobile development.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Flutter?","content":"Flutter is an open-source UI toolkit by Google for building cross-platform apps using Dart. It compiles to native code, allowing for high-performance applications across Android, iOS, Web, and Desktop."},{"heading":"Why Flutter?","content":"Flutter offers fast development with hot reload, beautiful UIs with built-in widgets, and single codebase deployment across platforms. It's used by Alibaba, BMW, and Google Ads."},{"heading":"1. Learn Dart Language","content":"Dart is Flutter’s programming language. Learn types, functions, async/await, classes, and null safety.","links":[{"text":"Dart Language Tour","href":"https://dart.dev/guides/language/language-tour"}],"code":"void greet(String name) => print('Hello, $name!');"},{"heading":"2. Set Up Flutter Environment","content":"Install Flutter SDK, Android Studio or VS Code, and configure emulators or real devices.","links":[{"text":"Install Flutter","href":"https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install"}]},{"heading":"3. Widgets - The Building Blocks","content":"Understand StatelessWidget vs StatefulWidget, build UIs with Column, Row, Text, Image, ListView, etc.","code":"class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {\n  @override\n  Widget build(BuildContext context) {\n    return MaterialApp(home: Text('Hello Flutter'));\n  }\n}"},{"heading":"4. Routing and Navigation","content":"Use Navigator 1.0 for basic navigation and Navigator 2.0 for deep linking and complex flows.","code":"Navigator.push(context, MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => SecondPage()));"},{"heading":"5. State Management","content":"Start with setState, then move to Provider, Riverpod, Bloc, MobX or GetX for large apps.","links":[{"text":"Provider Package","href":"https://pub.dev/packages/provider"}]},{"heading":"6. Themes and Custom Widgets","content":"Use ThemeData to customize your app's look. Build reusable widgets with parameters."},{"heading":"7. Forms and Validation","content":"Use `TextFormField`, `Form`, and validation logic for input handling.","code":"TextFormField(validator: (val) => val!.isEmpty ? 'Required' : null)"},{"heading":"8. Networking","content":"Use `http`, `dio`, or `graphql_flutter` for API calls and JSON decoding with `dart:convert`.","code":"var res = await http.get(Uri.parse('https://api.example.com'));"},{"heading":"9. Firebase Integration","content":"Use packages like `firebase_core`, `firebase_auth`, `cloud_firestore`, and `firebase_messaging`.","links":[{"text":"FlutterFire Docs","href":"https://firebase.flutter.dev/"}]},{"heading":"10. Animations","content":"Use `AnimationController`, `Tween`, and implicit animations like `AnimatedContainer` or libraries like `rive`."},{"heading":"11. Testing","content":"Use `flutter_test` for unit/widget tests and `integration_test` for E2E testing.","code":"testWidgets('Check text', (tester) async {\n  await tester.pumpWidget(MyApp());\n  expect(find.text('Hello'), findsOneWidget);\n});"},{"heading":"12. Publishing Your App","content":"Use `flutter build` to generate release APKs or IPAs, configure signing, and publish to Play Store/App Store."},{"heading":"13. Best Practices","content":"- Use modular architecture\n- Avoid business logic in widgets\n- Use lints and analyzer\n- Optimize rebuilds\n- Use const widgets where possible"}],"related":["ubuntu-roadmap","nextauthjs-roadmap","langchain-roadmap","nginx-roadmap","angular-roadmap"]},{"slug":"tensorflow-roadmap","title":"TensorFlow Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master TensorFlow in 2025 with this roadmap covering core TF, model building, data pipelines, deployment, optimization, and ecosystem tools.","sections":[{"heading":"What is TensorFlow?","content":"TensorFlow is a widely adopted open-source machine learning framework by Google for building and deploying ML models across platforms."},{"heading":"Why TensorFlow?","content":"TensorFlow offers performance, scalability, production readiness, and a robust ecosystem including Keras, TensorBoard, and TF Serving."},{"heading":"1. Install & Setup","content":"Install via pip or Conda; use virtual environments; optional GPU support (CUDA/cuDNN).","code":"pip install tensorflow\n# or GPU: tensorflow-gpu"},{"heading":"2. Tensor Basics & Eager Execution","content":"Learn tf.Tensor operations, shapes, broadcasting, and debugging with eager mode.","code":"import tensorflow as tf\nx = tf.constant([[1,2],[3,4]])\nprint(x.shape)"},{"heading":"3. Keras High‑Level API","content":"Build sequential or functional models using tf.keras.","code":"model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([\n  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='relu', input_shape=(20,)),\n  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)\n])"},{"heading":"4. Data Pipelines (tf.data)","content":"Use tf.data.Dataset to handle CSV, TFRecord, data augmentation, shuffling, and batching.","code":"ds = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((x_train, y_train))\n.ds.batch(32).shuffle(1000)"},{"heading":"5. Estimators & Custom Training","content":"Learn custom training loops with GradientTape and custom metrics/losses.","code":"with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n  pred = model(x)\n  loss = loss_fn(y, pred)\ngrad = tape.gradient(loss, model.trainable_variables)"},{"heading":"6. Callbacks & TensorBoard","content":"Use ModelCheckpoint, EarlyStopping, and TensorBoard for metrics and graph visualizations."},{"heading":"7. Transfer Learning","content":"Use pretrained models (e.g., MobileNet, ResNet) and fine-tune for custom tasks."},{"heading":"8. Model Evaluation & Metrics","content":"Evaluate models with precision, recall, ROC curves. Use tf.keras.metrics.*."},{"heading":"9. Hyperparameter Tuning","content":"Use Keras Tuner to find optimal architecture/hyperparameters."},{"heading":"10. Save & Export Models","content":"Save in SavedModel format; export to TF Lite, TF.js for various platforms."},{"heading":"11. TensorFlow Lite & TF.js","content":"Deploy to mobile (TFLite) or browser (TensorFlow.js).","code":"import tensorflow.lite as tflite\nconverter = tflite.TFLiteConverter.from_saved_model('saved/');"},{"heading":"12. Model Serving","content":"Use TensorFlow Serving or custom REST APIs for production deployment."},{"heading":"13. Performance Optimization","content":"Use mixed precision, graph optimization, XLA, and pruning."},{"heading":"14. Distributed Training","content":"Use tf.distribute strategies like MirroredStrategy and MultiWorkerMirroredStrategy."},{"heading":"15. TF Extended (TFX)","content":"Build ML pipelines with components like Data Validation, Trainer, and Serving."},{"heading":"16. Explainability & Interpretability","content":"Use TensorBoard Embedding Projector or integrate with LIME/SHAP."},{"heading":"17. Ecosystem Tools","content":"Use TensorFlow Hub, Addons, Model Garden, and Rails for advanced functionalities."},{"heading":"18. Security & Governance","content":"Apply model access control, data privacy, reproducibility, versioning."},{"heading":"19. Community & Tutorials","content":"Follow TensorFlow blog, GitHub, and community Slack/Reddit channels."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Modularize models, log everything, use GPU profiling, version datasets, and use reproducible pipelines"}],"related":["python-roadmap","github-roadmap","aws-roadmap","blockchain-roadmap","unreal-engine-roadmap"]},{"slug":"pytorch-roadmap","title":"PyTorch Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master PyTorch in 2025 with this roadmap covering core tensors, dynamic models, data loading, GPU acceleration, ecosystem tools, and deployment strategies.","sections":[{"heading":"What is PyTorch?","content":"PyTorch is an open-source deep learning framework by Facebook that offers dynamic computation graphs and Pythonic syntax, widely used in research and production."},{"heading":"Why PyTorch?","content":"PyTorch’s dynamic graph, ease of debugging, strong community support, and tools like TorchServe and TorchScript make it a top choice for ML engineers."},{"heading":"1. Install & Setup","content":"Install via pip or Conda with optional GPU support.","code":"pip install torch torchvision"},{"heading":"2. Tensors & Operations","content":"Learn tensor creation, indexing, slicing, reshaping, broadcasting, and autograd.","code":"import torch\na = torch.randn(3,3, requires_grad=True)"},{"heading":"3. Building Models (nn.Module)","content":"Build models by subclassing nn.Module with `forward` methods.","code":"class Net(nn.Module):\n  def __init__(self): super().__init__(); self.fc=nn.Linear(10,1)\n  def forward(self, x): return self.fc(x)"},{"heading":"4. Dataset & DataLoader","content":"Create custom Dataset classes and use DataLoader for batching, shuffling, and multi-worker loading.","code":"loader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size=32, shuffle=True)"},{"heading":"5. Loss & Optimization","content":"Use nn.CrossEntropyLoss, MSELoss, and optimizers like SGD or Adam.","code":"criterion = nn.MSELoss()\noptimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters())"},{"heading":"6. Training Loop & Backprop","content":"Implement training loop with forward pass, loss calculation, backward(), and optimizer.step().","code":"for x,y in loader:\n  optimizer.zero_grad()\n  out = model(x)\n  loss = criterion(out,y)\n  loss.backward()\n  optimizer.step()"},{"heading":"7. Validation & Metrics","content":"Evaluate on val data, compute metrics like accuracy, F1 score, and use torch.no_grad() to disable gradients."},{"heading":"8. Checkpoints & Saving","content":"Save and load `state_dict()` for model and optimizer.","code":"torch.save(model.state_dict(), 'model.pth')"},{"heading":"9. GPU & Multi-GPU Support","content":"Use `.to(device)`, DataParallel, DistributedDataParallel (DDP)."},{"heading":"10. Custom Modules & Extensions","content":"Write custom nn.Modules, autograd functions, or C++ extensions."},{"heading":"11. Mixed Precision Training","content":"Use `torch.cuda.amp` for faster FP16 training."},{"heading":"12. Visualization (TensorBoard & TorchVision)","content":"Use `torch.utils.tensorboard` or `matplotlib` to visualize metrics and model outputs."},{"heading":"13. TorchScript & JIT","content":"Trace or script models for deployment without Python dependencies."},{"heading":"14. Model Serving (TorchServe)","content":"Deploy models via REST endpoints using TorchServe."},{"heading":"15. Transfer Learning & Fine-Tuning","content":"Use torchvision pretrained models (ResNet, BERT, etc.) and fine-tune."},{"heading":"16. Distributed & Pipeline Parallelism","content":"Use torch.distributed and pipeline/micro-batching for large-scale training."},{"heading":"17. Ecosystem Tools","content":"Explore PyTorch Lightning, Catalyst, Hugging Face Transformers, and Ignite for cleaner workflows."},{"heading":"18. Quantization & ONNX","content":"Apply static/dynamic quantization, export to ONNX for cross-framework portability."},{"heading":"19. Community & Research","content":"Follow torch.org, GitHub issues, forums, and participate in ML competitions."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use seed setting, log hyperparameters, modularize code, test reproducibility, and profile bottlenecks"}],"related":["hardhat-roadmap","redux-roadmap","google-cloud-roadmap","netlify-roadmap","mysql-roadmap"]},{"slug":"opencv-roadmap","title":"OpenCV Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master OpenCV in 2025 with this roadmap covering computer vision basics, image/video processing, feature detection, ML integration, and deployment.","sections":[{"heading":"What is OpenCV?","content":"OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision Library) is a popular C++ (with Python bindings) library for real-time image and video processing."},{"heading":"Why OpenCV?","content":"OpenCV offers fast performance, portability, a wide range of CV functions, and easy integration with other libraries like NumPy, TensorFlow, and PyTorch."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Install with pip (`opencv-python`), or build from source for GPU support."},{"heading":"2. Image I/O and Display","content":"Read/write images and display windows.","code":"import cv2\nimg = cv2.imread('image.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)\ncv2.imshow('Image', img)\ncv2.waitKey(0)\ncv2.destroyAllWindows()"},{"heading":"3. Basic Image Processing","content":"Perform grayscale conversion, resizing, thresholds, blurring.","code":"gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\nblur = cv2.GaussianBlur(gray, (5,5), 0)"},{"heading":"4. Edge & Corner Detection","content":"Use Canny edge and Harris/shi‑Tomasi corner detectors.","code":"edges = cv2.Canny(gray, 50, 150)\ncorners = cv2.goodFeaturesToTrack(gray, 100, 0.01, 10)"},{"heading":"5. Contours & Shape Analysis","content":"Detect contours, compute areas, bounding shapes.","code":"contours, _ = cv2.findContours(thresh, cv2.RETR_TREE, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)"},{"heading":"6. Feature Matching","content":"Use ORB, SIFT/SURF, BFMatcher for image matching and stitching."},{"heading":"7. Object Detection & Classification","content":"Load pre-trained DNNs (like YOLO, SSD) and perform detections.","code":"net = cv2.dnn.readNet('yolov4.weights', 'yolov4.cfg')"},{"heading":"8. Camera Calibration & 3D Vision","content":"Perform camera calibration, stereovision, and pose estimation."},{"heading":"9. Face Detection & Recognition","content":"Use Haar cascades or `face_recognition` integration."},{"heading":"10. Video Processing","content":"Read/write video frames, track objects.","code":"cap = cv2.VideoCapture('vid.mp4')\nwhile cap.isOpened():\n  ret, frame = cap.read()\n  if not ret: break"},{"heading":"11. Performance Optimization","content":"Use threading, GPU (CUDA), and compiled builds."},{"heading":"12. Machine Learning & Deep Learning Integration","content":"Use DNN module or integrate with TensorFlow/PyTorch models."},{"heading":"13. Deployment","content":"Deploy on edge devices (Raspberry Pi), or mobile (OpenCV Android/iOS)."},{"heading":"14. ROS & Robotics","content":"Use OpenCV with ROS for robot vision pipelines."},{"heading":"15. GUI Interaction","content":"Use HighGUI trackbars and mouse callbacks."},{"heading":"16. Documentation & Community","content":"Rely on opencv.org documentation and GitHub community."},{"heading":"17. Best Practices","content":"- Use ROI to reduce computation\n- Avoid large memory copies\n- Pre-compile cascade models\n- Profile with `cv2.getTickCount()`"}],"related":["sentry-roadmap","strapi-roadmap","java-roadmap","aws-roadmap","new-relic-roadmap"]},{"slug":"unity-roadmap","title":"Unity Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Unity development in 2025 with this roadmap covering core engine concepts, scripting, UI, physics, animation, packaging, and XR/AR expansions.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Unity?","content":"Unity is a powerful cross-platform game engine for building 2D, 3D, AR, VR, and interactive experiences using C# scripting."},{"heading":"Why Unity?","content":"Unity offers a strong ecosystem, multi-platform deployment, asset store, and community—ideal for indie devs and enterprise projects."},{"heading":"1. Install & Setup","content":"Install Unity Hub, choose LTS version, and configure Android/iOS modules."},{"heading":"2. Editor Basics","content":"Learn Unity Editor layout: Scene, Game views, Hierarchy, Inspector."},{"heading":"3. GameObjects & Components","content":"Create GameObjects, add Components for Transform, Rigidbody, Renderer."},{"heading":"4. Scripting in C