draft & publish mode and schedule publications."},{"heading":"14. API Customization & Middlewares","content":"Use lifecycle hooks, custom middlewares in routes."},{"heading":"15. Security & CORS","content":"Configure CORS, limit API rate, sanitize inputs."},{"heading":"16. Testing Strapi APIs","content":"Use Jest and `supertest` to test controllers and services."},{"heading":"17. Deployment Strategies","content":"Deploy in containers, DigitalOcean, Heroku, Railway; configure SSL and env vars."},{"heading":"18. Scaling & Performance","content":"Use Redis caching, database optimization, and horizontal scaling."},{"heading":"19. Monitoring & Analytics","content":"Set up logging, analytics, healthchecks (PM2, Sentry)."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep business logic in services\n- Use env-specific configs\n- Secure endpoints properly\n- Document custom APIs"}],"related":["tensorflow-roadmap","rust-roadmap","django-roadmap","redux-roadmap","graphql-roadmap"]},{"slug":"contentful-roadmap","title":"Contentful Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Contentful in 2025 with this roadmap covering headless CMS setup, content modeling, APIs, integrations, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Contentful?","content":"Contentful is a cloud-based headless CMS that delivers content via RESTful and GraphQL APIs, enabling content infrastructure across multiple platforms."},{"heading":"Why Contentful?","content":"It separates content from presentation, supports powerful content modeling, and integrates with modern frameworks and services."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Sign up at Contentful, create a space, define environments (e.g., development, production)."},{"heading":"2. Content Modeling","content":"Define content types (e.g., Article, Author), fields, validations, and references."},{"heading":"3. Content Delivery API","content":"Use CDA for published content—install `contentful` SDK and query entries.","code":"import { createClient } from 'contentful';\nconst client = createClient({ space, accessToken });\nconst entries = await client.getEntries({ content_type: 'article' });"},{"heading":"4. Content Management API","content":"Use CMA for programmatic content editing (e.g., seeding, migrations)."},{"heading":"5. GraphQL API","content":"Enable GraphQL endpoint, write queries for optimized content retrieval."},{"heading":"6. Webhooks & Automation","content":"Configure webhooks for publish, delete events and integrate with Netlify functions or Zapier."},{"heading":"7. Rich Text & Assets","content":"Use rich-text fields and asset uploads with transformation URLs."},{"heading":"8. SDKs & Framework Integrations","content":"Integrate with React (`useEffect`), Next.js, Gatsby, Nuxt, or native via SDKs."},{"heading":"9. Preview Workflows","content":"Enable preview API for unpublished content with secure tokens."},{"heading":"10. Localization & Multi-region","content":"Use locale settings, localized field values, and delivery based on region."},{"heading":"11. Roles & Permissions","content":"Configure roles, API tokens, and granular access control settings."},{"heading":"12. Content Versioning & History","content":"Use Contentful's versioning system to view history, rollback drafts."},{"heading":"13. App Framework & Extensions","content":"Build custom editor extensions using UI Extensions SDK.","links":[{"text":"Contentful UI Extensions","href":"https://www.contentful.com/developers/docs/extensibility/ui-extensions/"}]},{"heading":"14. Environments & Migrations","content":"Manage content migrations with `contentful-migration` CLI."},{"heading":"15. Testing & Staging","content":"Seed content via CMA in staging environments for testing."},{"heading":"16. Performance Optimization","content":"Use content synchronization, caching, selective fields, and query optimization."},{"heading":"17. CI/CD Integration","content":"Leverage webhooks to trigger builds or deployments on content updates."},{"heading":"18. Analytics & Insights","content":"Use Contentful’s app insights or integrate Google Analytics for content usage."},{"heading":"19. Best Practices","content":"- Keep models modular\n- Use environments wisely\n- Limit field size\n- Purge stale assets regularly"},{"heading":"20. Community & Support","content":"Use Contentful’s community forum, StackOverflow, official docs, and Contentful University."}],"related":["angular-roadmap","apache-roadmap","nextjs-roadmap","github-roadmap","docker-roadmap"]},{"slug":"sanity-io-roadmap","title":"Sanity.io Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Sanity.io in 2025 with this roadmap covering studio setup, schema, GROQ, structured content, deployment, and integrations.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Sanity.io?","content":"Sanity.io is a flexible headless CMS with real-time collaboration, structured content, custom editors, and live preview."},{"heading":"Why Sanity.io?","content":"It’s fully customizable, real-time, and supports integrations with modern frameworks and structured content modeling."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Install CLI: `npm install -g @sanity/cli`; run `sanity init` to create project."},{"heading":"2. Defining Schemas","content":"Define document and object types in schemas using JavaScript.","code":"export default { name: 'author', title: 'Author', type: 'document', fields: [{ name: 'name', type: 'string' }] };"},{"heading":"3. Content Studio Customization","content":"Customize desk structure, input components, and preview panes."},{"heading":"4. GROQ & Data Queries","content":"Query content with GROQ syntax.","code":"const data = await client.fetch('*[_type == \"post\"]{title, body}');"},{"heading":"5. Structured Text & Portable Text","content":"Use Portable Text for rich text rendering with custom serializers."},{"heading":"6. Asset Management","content":"Manage images, files, and use image pipelines for transformations."},{"heading":"7. Real-time Collaboration","content":"Use real-time editing and user presence in Studio."},{"heading":"8. Versioning & History","content":"Use document revisions, time-travel, and rollback features."},{"heading":"9. API & Frontend Integration","content":"Use `@sanity/client` in React, Next.js, or Vue projects."},{"heading":"10. Webhooks & Triggered Workflows","content":"Use webhooks for rebuilds, external systems, or serverless functions."},{"heading":"11. Plugins Ecosystem","content":"Use official and community plugins—create or customize plugins via Sanity Studio."},{"heading":"12. GraphQL API","content":"Enable GraphQL API via plugin and use GraphQL queries."},{"heading":"13. Authentication & ACL","content":"Use role-based access control and single sign-on (SSO) for team management."},{"heading":"14. Localization Support","content":"Implement multi-language content models and locale handling."},{"heading":"15. Preview Environments","content":"Enable live preview in Studio and client apps."},{"heading":"16. Deploying Studio","content":"Deploy Studio on Netlify, Vercel, or custom servers."},{"heading":"17. Performance Optimization","content":"Use query projection, CDN caching, and image pipelines."},{"heading":"18. CI/CD & Migrations","content":"Manage schema migrations and deploy using GitOps workflows."},{"heading":"19. Monitoring & Analytics","content":"Use Studio analytics, usage logs, and external monitoring."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use modular schema files\n- Validate input types\n- Clean up unused content types\n- Use structured content for flexibility"}],"related":["bootstrap-roadmap","truffle-roadmap","cypress-roadmap","metamask-roadmap","kubernetes-roadmap"]},{"slug":"prisma-roadmap","title":"Prisma Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Prisma in 2025 with this roadmap covering setup, schema modeling, migrations, querying, relations, performance, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Prisma?","content":"Prisma is a next-generation ORM for Node.js and TypeScript that makes database access type-safe, performant, and easy to maintain."},{"heading":"Why Prisma?","content":"It provides type-safe queries, auto-generated clients, intuitive schema, migrations, and a developer-friendly ecosystem."},{"heading":"1. Setup & Initialization","content":"Install via `npm install prisma @prisma/client`, then initialize with `npx prisma init`."},{"heading":"2. Data Modeling (schema.prisma)","content":"Define models, fields, types, relations, constraints.","code":"model User {\n  id    Int     @id @default(autoincrement())\n  name  String\n  posts Post[]\n}"},{"heading":"3. Migrations","content":"Use `npx prisma migrate dev` to create migration files and update database."},{"heading":"4. Prisma Client Queries","content":"Run CRUD operations with type-safe generated client.","code":"const user = await prisma.user.create({ data: { name: 'Alice' } });"},{"heading":"5. Relations & Nested Writes","content":"Use `include`, `select`, and nested create/update.","code":"await prisma.user.create({ data: { name: 'Bob', posts: { create: [{ title: 'Hello' }] } } });"},{"heading":"6. Aggregations & Filters","content":"Use `where`, `orderBy`, `groupBy`, and aggregate functions."},{"heading":"7. Transactions & Batching","content":"Use `$transaction` to run atomic operations."},{"heading":"8. Performance & Indexing","content":"Optimize queries, add database indexes, and monitor query plans."},{"heading":"9. Middleware & Logging","content":"Use Prisma middleware and client logging to debug and profile."},{"heading":"10. Runtime Types & Validation","content":"Combine with Zod or Yup for input validation."},{"heading":"11. Seeding Data","content":"Seed databases via `prisma db seed` using JavaScript/TypeScript."},{"heading":"12. Working with Multiple Databases","content":"Configure multiple database providers in schema and clients."},{"heading":"13. TypeScript & IntelliSense","content":"Enjoy full type safety and enhanced IDE experience."},{"heading":"14. Migrations in Deploy","content":"Run migrations in CI/CD pipelines with `prisma migrate deploy`."},{"heading":"15. Error Handling","content":"Catch known errors like `Prisma.PrismaClientKnownRequestError`."},{"heading":"16. Versioning & Schema Tracking","content":"Track migration history and apply incremental changes."},{"heading":"17. Best Practices","content":"- Keep model relationships lean\n- Avoid over-fetching with select\n- Use transactions for multi-step operations\n- Log and monitor query performance"}],"related":["strapi-roadmap","jest-roadmap","kotlin-roadmap","nextjs-roadmap","blockchain-roadmap"]},{"slug":"sequelize-roadmap","title":"Sequelize Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Sequelize in 2025 with this roadmap covering setup, models, relations, migrations, querying strategies, performance, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Sequelize?","content":"Sequelize is a promise-based ORM for Node.js that supports multiple SQL dialects, offering flexible querying and migrations."},{"heading":"Why Sequelize?","content":"It offers extensive SQL features, model definition, database migrations, and works well with both JavaScript and TypeScript."},{"heading":"1. Setup & Configuration","content":"Install via `npm install sequelize sequelize-cli`, configure dialect in `config.json`."},{"heading":"2. Defining Models","content":"Use `sequelize.define` or ES6 class extends `Model`.","code":"class User extends Model {}\nUser.init({ name: DataTypes.STRING }, { sequelize, modelName: 'user' });"},{"heading":"3. Migrations & Seeders","content":"Generate migrations via `sequelize-cli`, alter schema and seed data."},{"heading":"4. Associations","content":"Define `hasMany`, `belongsTo`, `belongsToMany`, `hasOne` relationships.","code":"User.hasMany(Post);\nPost.belongsTo(User);"},{"heading":"5. CRUD Operations","content":"Use `Model.create`, `findOne`, `findAll`, `update`, `destroy`."},{"heading":"6. Complex Queries","content":"Use `where`, `include`, `order`, `group`, `raw` options."},{"heading":"7. Transactions","content":"Run atomic operations using `sequelize.transaction()`."},{"heading":"8. Scopes & Hooks","content":"Use `defaultScope`, custom scopes and lifecycle hooks (`beforeCreate` etc.)."},{"heading":"9. Raw SQL Queries","content":"Run raw queries via `sequelize.query`, useful for complex cases."},{"heading":"10. Eager vs Lazy Loading","content":"Control associations fetching behavior using `include` and `lazy getters`."},{"heading":"11. Pagination Strategies","content":"Use `limit`, `offset`, and cursor pagination with `order`."},{"heading":"12. Migration in Deploy","content":"Use `sequelize db:migrate` and `db:seed:all` in production CI."},{"heading":"13. Performance & Indexing","content":"Add indexes in model definition and optimize heavy queries."},{"heading":"14. Logging & Error Handling","content":"Enable `logging` option, catch Sequelize-specific errors."},{"heading":"15. Working in TypeScript","content":"Use ABM classes with `sequelize-typescript` for better typing."},{"heading":"16. Migrations with Types","content":"Type-check migrations using TS, maintain types with models."},{"heading":"17. Best Practices","content":"- Use hooks wisely\n- Keep logic out of migrations\n- Avoid circular associations\n- Use transactions for data integrity"}],"related":["flutter-roadmap","django-roadmap","swift-roadmap","opencv-roadmap","php-roadmap"]},{"slug":"supabase-roadmap","title":"Supabase Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Supabase in 2025 with this roadmap covering setup, database modeling, authentication, storage, functions, client libraries, deployment, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Supabase?","content":"Supabase is an open-source Firebase alternative offering PostgreSQL database, real-time subscriptions, authentication, storage, and edge Functions."},{"heading":"Why Supabase?","content":"It provides a full backend-as-a-service with SQL support, real-time capabilities, built-in authentication, and seamless integration with modern frameworks."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Create a free project on supabase.com, get API keys and connection string, and install client via `npm install @supabase/supabase-js`."},{"heading":"2. Database Modeling","content":"Design tables, use PostgreSQL types, define relationships and indexes in Supabase Studio or via SQL editor."},{"heading":"3. Row-Level Security (RLS)","content":"Enable RLS and implement policies to secure table access per user roles."},{"heading":"4. Authentication","content":"Use Supabase Auth for sign-up, social logins, magic links, and integrate `useSession()` client-side.","code":"const { user, session, error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({ email, password });"},{"heading":"5. Client CRUD Operations","content":"Use `supabase.from('table').select().insert().update().delete()` for data operations.","code":"const { data, error } = await supabase\n  .from('todos')\n  .select('*')\n  .eq('user_id', user.id);\n\nconst { error: insertError } = await supabase\n  .from('todos')\n  .insert([{ title: 'Task' }]);"},{"heading":"6. Real-time Subscriptions","content":"Subscribe to DB changes using `supabase.channel()` and events.","code":"supabase\n  .channel('public:todos')\n  .on('postgres_changes', { event: '*', schema: 'public', table: 'todos' }, payload => console.log(payload))\n  .subscribe();"},{"heading":"7. Storage: Files & Media","content":"Use storage buckets for file upload/download with ACL support.","code":"const { data, error } = await supabase.storage\n  .from('avatars')\n  .upload('user123.png', file);"},{"heading":"8. Functions (Edge Functions)","content":"Write server-side logic with Supabase Functions using Deno/TypeScript.","code":"export async function handler(req) {\n  const data = await req.json();\n  return new Response('Hello ' + data.name);\n}"},{"heading":"9. API Clients & Framework Integrations","content":"Use official clients for React, Next.js, Vue, Svelte, Flutter, and integrate with SSR."},{"heading":"10. Auth & DB Triggers","content":"Use triggers and `auth.users` events in SQL or Functions to react to auth/sign-up."},{"heading":"11. REST & GraphQL API","content":"Use auto-generated REST via PostgREST and GraphQL plugins for API usage."},{"heading":"12. Supabase Studio & Admin","content":"Use Studio to manage schema, inspect logs, monitor performance, and analytics."},{"heading":"13. Performance & Scaling","content":"Use indexes, partitions, caching, and upgrade plans for production scaling."},{"heading":"14. Testing & CI/CD","content":"Write integration tests, use Docker or Supabase local, automate migrations in CI."},{"heading":"15. Security Best Practices","content":"Enforce RLS, minimize service role usage, rotate keys, use HTTPS."},{"heading":"16. Monitoring & Observability","content":"Monitor database, error logs, and audit usage; integrate with Sentry, DataDog."},{"heading":"17. Backup & Restore","content":"Use database backups, export snapshots, and test restores regularly."},{"heading":"18. Versioning & Migrations","content":"Use `supabase migrations` CLI to version schema and track tooling environments."},{"heading":"19. Community & Ecosystem","content":"Use Supabase Auth, Slack, GitHub, and discover community plugins and tools."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep RLS policies tight\n- Validate inputs in Edge Functions\n- Use real-time updates wisely\n- Monitor usage to control costs"}],"related":["recoil-roadmap","javascript-roadmap","sequelize-roadmap","nginx-roadmap","storybook-roadmap"]},{"slug":"hasura-roadmap","title":"Hasura GraphQL Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Hasura in 2025 with this roadmap covering GraphQL engine setup, data sources, permissions, event triggers, remote schema stitching, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Hasura?","content":"Hasura is an open-source GraphQL engine that auto-generates realtime GraphQL APIs on Postgres (and compatible databases) with built-in authorization and event triggers."},{"heading":"Why Hasura?","content":"It lets you launch full-featured APIs and realtime subscriptions with minimal code, while supporting customization via remote schemas, actions, metadata migrations, and more."},{"heading":"1. Setup & Initialization","content":"Install via Docker or CLI (`hasura init`), connect to PostgreSQL or RDMS."},{"heading":"2. Database Modeling","content":"Use Hasura Console to create tables, relationships, enums, views and manage schema."},{"heading":"3. Auto-generated CRUD GraphQL","content":"Query and mutate data through auto-generated queries/mutations with arguments, filters, ordering, and pagination."},{"heading":"4. Realtime Queries","content":"Use GraphQL subscriptions to get live updates on table changes."},{"heading":"5. Authentication & Authorization","content":"Set up JWT auth (Auth0, Firebase, custom), configure role-based permissions per table/action."},{"heading":"6. Remote Schemas & Actions","content":"Integrate external GraphQL APIs via remote schemas and extend logic with custom actions."},{"heading":"7. Event Triggers & Scheduled Jobs","content":"Use `event_triggers` to invoke webhooks or serverless functions on DB changes."},{"heading":"8. Hasura Console & CLI","content":"Manage metadata, migrations, and configs via Console UI or CLI (`hasura migrate apply`/`export`)."},{"heading":"9. Metadata Migrations & CodeGen","content":"Track migrations in version control using metadata migrations and `hasura codegen` for type-safe client usage."},{"heading":"10. Relationships & Joins","content":"Define foreign key relationships automatically and fetch nested results in single query."},{"heading":"11. Caching & Performance","content":"Use query cache, persisted queries, connection pooling, and Cloudflare, Apollo caching layers."},{"heading":"12. Monitoring & Logs","content":"Use Hasura Cloud or self-hosted logs, Prometheus, Grafana integration."},{"heading":"13. CI/CD & Environments","content":"Use GitHub Actions or GitLab CI to track migrations, metadata in different environments."},{"heading":"14. Security Best Practices","content":"Use least-privilege roles, environment isolation, secure metadata endpoints."},{"heading":"15. Real-world Integration Patterns","content":"Combine Hasura with serverless, Postgres functions, REST APIs, and actions to build full apps."},{"heading":"16. Frontend Usage","content":"Use Apollo Client, Urql, or Relay with Hasura for queries, subscriptions, optimistic UI."},{"heading":"17. Remote Joins & Custom Logic","content":"Join across remote schemas and add business logic using actions."},{"heading":"18. Federation & Stitching","content":"Compose GraphQL services under one unified API via remote schemas and stitching."},{"heading":"19. Scaling & High Availability","content":"Use replicas, read scaling, metadata caching, and auto-scaling clusters."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep metadata in version control\n- Use migrations for schema changes\n- Configure roles and permissions explicitly\n- Monitor performance and costs"}],"related":["nextjs-roadmap","sql-roadmap","cpp-roadmap","csharp-roadmap","supabase-roadmap"]},{"slug":"elasticsearch-roadmap","title":"Elasticsearch Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Elasticsearch in 2025 with this roadmap covering setup, data modeling, querying, aggregation, scaling, monitoring, and search best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Elasticsearch?","content":"Elasticsearch is a distributed, RESTful search and analytics engine built on Apache Lucene, designed for fast full-text search and data analytics."},{"heading":"Why Elasticsearch?","content":"It enables scalable, real-time search, analytics, and observability, with powerful querying, aggregation, geo, and machine learning features."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Cluster Setup","content":"Install via Docker or apt/yum, configure `elasticsearch.yml`, allocate heap, set up single/multi-node cluster."},{"heading":"2. Index & Mapping","content":"Create indices, define mappings, data types, analyzers, tokenizers, ensure correct field definitions."},{"heading":"3. Indexing Data","content":"Bulk index documents using REST API or client libraries (.NET, Java, JS, Python)."},{"heading":"4. Basic Queries","content":"Use `match`, `term`, `range`, and `exists` queries."},{"heading":"5. Full-text Search","content":"Use `match_phrase`, `multi_match`, `fuzziness`, query analyzers."},{"heading":"6. Aggregations","content":"Use `terms`, `date_histogram`, `range`, `stats` aggregations for analytics."},{"heading":"7. Pagination & Sorting","content":"Use `from/size`, `search_after`, or `scroll` APIs for large sets."},{"heading":"8. Highlighting & Suggestions","content":"Include highlights and `suggest` for autocomplete and did-you-mean features."},{"heading":"9. Analysis & Tokenization","content":"Customize token filters, tokenizers, stemming, stop words."},{"heading":"10. Scaling & Sharding","content":"Understand primary/replica shards, reindexing, index templates, rollover policies."},{"heading":"11. Monitoring & Alerting","content":"Use Kibana, Elastic Stack monitoring, Elasticsearch Exporter for Prometheus."},{"heading":"12. Security","content":"Enable TLS, authentication with Elastic Stack Security or OpenID, role-based access control."},{"heading":"13. Ingest Pipelines","content":"Use ingest pipelines, Logstash, Beats; parse and transform, enrich documents."},{"heading":"14. Geo & Graph Searches","content":"Use `geo_point`, geohash, geo-aggregation; implement Graph API."},{"heading":"15. Relevance Tuning","content":"Adjust `boost`, `function_score`, `script_score` and use learning-to-rank."},{"heading":"16. Index Lifecycle Management","content":"Use ILM policies to manage retention, rollovers, deletion."},{"heading":"17. Backups & Snapshots","content":"Take snapshots to S3, Azure, or shared FS."},{"heading":"18. Performance Tuning","content":"Tune refresh interval, merge policy, caching, thread pool."},{"heading":"19. Kibana & Visualization","content":"Build dashboards, use Kibana Lens and Visualize tool."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Design correct mapping early\n- Use aliases to manage indices\n- Monitor cluster health\n- Use ILM to automate maintenance tasks"}],"related":["sentry-roadmap","sequelize-roadmap","threejs-roadmap","laravel-roadmap","linux-roadmap"]},{"slug":"algolia-roadmap","title":"Algolia Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Algolia in 2025 with this roadmap covering search indexing, queries, relevance tuning, analytics, integrations, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Algolia?","content":"Algolia is a hosted search-as-a-service platform that delivers fast, customizable, and scalable search experiences via RESTful or JavaScript APIs."},{"heading":"Why Algolia?","content":"It provides developer-centric features like typo tolerance, instant results, faceting, and analytics without requiring custom infrastructure."},{"heading":"1. Setup & API Keys","content":"Create an Algolia account, set up an index, and obtain Admin and Search API keys."},{"heading":"2. Indexing Data","content":"Push data via the dashboard, REST API, or helper libraries (JavaScript, Python, Ruby).","code":"await index.saveObjects([{ objectID: '1', title: 'Hello' }]);"},{"heading":"3. Basic Search Queries","content":"Use `index.search('query')` with options like `hitsPerPage`, `attributesToRetrieve`.","code":"const res = await index.search('test', { facets: ['category'] });"},{"heading":"4. Faceting & Filtering","content":"Use facets, filters, numeric filters, tag-based faceting, and combined filters."},{"heading":"5. Typo Tolerance & Synonyms","content":"Configure typo-tolerance level and add synonym rules for better relevance."},{"heading":"6. Pagination & Infinite Scroll","content":"Handle pagination using `page`, `hitsPerPage`, `cursor` or `whenPaged` in InstantSearch."},{"heading":"7. Ranking & Relevance Tuning","content":"Customize ranking via attributes, custom ranking, geo ranking, and query rules."},{"heading":"8. InstantSearch UI Integration","content":"Use InstantSearch.js or UI libraries for React, Vue, Angular for ready-to-use components."},{"heading":"9. Analytics & Insights","content":"Use Algolia analytics dashboard for popular queries, zero-results, A/B testing."},{"heading":"10. A/B Testing","content":"Run A/B experiments to compare ranking settings or UI changes."},{"heading":"11. Personalization","content":"Use Algolia Personalization API to tailor results to user behavior."},{"heading":"12. Geo-Search","content":"Search by location with `aroundLatLng`, bounding boxes and geofacets."},{"heading":"13. Typing & Dictionary Customization","content":"Add stop words, plurals, accents, and handle special languages."},{"heading":"14. Query Rules & Merchandising","content":"Set up query rules for promotions, banners, or result redirects."},{"heading":"15. Securing Search","content":"Generate scoped API keys, restrict via filters and expiration."},{"heading":"16. Front-End Performance","content":"Debounce input, lazy-load results, use cache & highlighting."},{"heading":"17. Mobile & Voice Search","content":"Use InstantSearch Native or adapt UI for voice assistants."},{"heading":"18. Monitoring & Alerts","content":"Track search health, latency, frequent zero-results and alert anomalies."},{"heading":"19. Multi-Index & Federated Search","content":"Search across multiple indices and display combined results."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Design searchable attributes concisely\n- Use typo‑tolerance smartly\n- Monitor analytics and refine\n- Secure API keys properly"}],"related":["tailwindcss-roadmap","openai-api-roadmap","cpp-roadmap","webrtc-roadmap","react-native-roadmap"]},{"slug":"vercel-roadmap","title":"Vercel Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Vercel in 2025 with this roadmap covering deployment, performance optimization, serverless, integrations, and edge functions.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Vercel?","content":"Vercel is a frontend deployment platform optimized for static sites, frameworks like Next.js, edge functions, and global CDN delivery."},{"heading":"Why Vercel?","content":"It provides zero-config deployments, best-in-class performance, automatic scaling, previews, and integration with Git workflows."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Install CLI via `npm i -g vercel`, link your project with `vercel login` and `vercel init`."},{"heading":"2. Framework Integration","content":"Deploy Next.js, Gatsby, Hugo, SvelteKit, or static HTML projects."},{"heading":"3. Git Integration & Previews","content":"Automatic deployments on PRs/branches, preview URLs, comments, and sharing."},{"heading":"4. Custom Domains & SSL","content":"Add domains, manage DNS, auto-generate SSL certificates."},{"heading":"5. Serverless Functions","content":"Deploy API endpoints via `api/*.js`/`ts`, auto-scaled, region-aware."},{"heading":"6. Edge Functions & Middleware","content":"Use `middleware.js` and edge functions for routing, headers, geolocation."},{"heading":"7. Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)","content":"Use `revalidate` in Next.js to regenerate static pages incrementally."},{"heading":"8. Image Optimization","content":"Use `next/image` with on-demand resizing and formats (AVIF, WebP)."},{"heading":"9. Analytics & Real User Metrics","content":"Enable Vercel Analytics to track real-user data (RUM)."},{"heading":"10. Performance Caching & Headers","content":"Set `cache-control`, leverage CDNs, custom headers and email."},{"heading":"11. Environment Variables","content":"Use Development, Preview, and Production env groups securely."},{"heading":"12. Monitoring & Logs","content":"Access logs, performance insights, error traces in dashboard."},{"heading":"13. Builds & Custom Build Steps","content":"Use `vercel.json` to define builds, install commands, output targets."},{"heading":"14. Edge Caching & Rewrites","content":"Use headers/rewrites/redirects to customize routing and cache behavior."},{"heading":"15. Preview Deployments & Share Links","content":"Share live preview URLs with stakeholders for feedback."},{"heading":"16. Monorepo Support","content":"Configure workspace roots, build targets, multiple projects."},{"heading":"17. Internationalization (i18n)","content":"Use Vercel’s i18n support with framework-level routing."},{"heading":"18. Cost & Usage Monitoring","content":"Track usage, bandwidth, build minutes across deployments."},{"heading":"19. Advanced Integrations","content":"Use edge middleware, headless CMS integration, authentication, analytics."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use preview deployments for QA\n- Optimize image and CDN configs\n- Monitor logs in production\n- Use edge functions sparingly and efficiently"}],"related":["elasticsearch-roadmap","supabase-roadmap","react-native-roadmap","metamask-roadmap","expressjs-roadmap"]},{"slug":"netlify-roadmap","title":"Netlify Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Netlify in 2025 with this roadmap covering deployments, CI/CD, serverless functions, edge capabilities, integrations, and performance optimization.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Netlify?","content":"Netlify is a cloud-based platform for deploying and hosting modern web projects, offering build automation, edge CDN, and serverless functions out of the box."},{"heading":"Why Netlify?","content":"It enables developers to deploy sites directly from Git with continuous deployment, instant rollbacks, global CDN, and built-in serverless support."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Sign up, link a Git repo (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket), and Netlify auto-detects and builds your project."},{"heading":"2. Build & Deploy Settings","content":"Configure build commands, publish directory, and environment variables."},{"heading":"3. Branch Deploys & Deploy Previews","content":"Automatically build preview URLs for pull requests and branches for quick testing."},{"heading":"4. Serverless Functions","content":"Add functions under `netlify/functions/`, written in Node.js, with zero configuration.","code":"exports.handler = async (event) => { return { statusCode: 200, body: JSON.stringify({ msg: 'Hello World' }) }; }"},{"heading":"5. Redirects & Rewrites","content":"Use `_redirects` or `netlify.toml` to handle routing, rewrites, proxies, and SPA fallback."},{"heading":"6. Edge Handlers","content":"Deploy edge middleware for A/B testing, auth, geotargeting, and custom headers."},{"heading":"7. Form Handling & Identity","content":"Use Netlify’s built‑in form handling and Identity for user signup/login flows."},{"heading":"8. Functions: Background & Scheduled","content":"Use `schedule` triggers in `netlify.toml` or background functions for long-running tasks."},{"heading":"9. Environment Variables & Secrets","content":"Manage secure env vars per branch or production via Netlify UI or CLI."},{"heading":"10. Plugin Ecosystem","content":"Use community plugins for image optimization, sitemap generation, linting, performance checks."},{"heading":"11. Custom Domains & SSL","content":"Add domains, manage DNS, and provision SSL certificates automatically."},{"heading":"12. Performance Monitoring","content":"Use Netlify Analytics or integrate with third-party tools to monitor speed and traffic."},{"heading":"13. Split Testing & A/B","content":"Run experiments using `split-testing` plugin or edge handlers."},{"heading":"14. Build Plugins & CLI","content":"Create custom build plugins, automate tasks, and use Netlify CLI for local dev."},{"heading":"15. Role-Based Access","content":"Manage team roles, permissions, and deploy settings."},{"heading":"16. Gatsby/Next Integration","content":"Use Static Generation, Server-side functions, and ISR on Netlify optimized for popular frameworks."},{"heading":"17. JAMstack Best Practices","content":"- Use lean JS bundles, lazy-load assets, leverage CDN; ensure build output is static-first."},{"heading":"18. CI/CD & Testing","content":"Use Netlify builds in CI pipelines; integrate unit tests via build plugins."},{"heading":"19. Build Contexts","content":"Customize build behavior per context (deploy previews, production, branches)."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use edge handlers sparingly\n- Monitor functions usage\n- Clean secrets between branches\n- Automate rollbacks via deploy previews"}],"related":["cpp-roadmap","firebase-roadmap","zustand-roadmap","react-roadmap","python-roadmap"]},{"slug":"heroku-roadmap","title":"Heroku Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Heroku in 2025 with this roadmap covering application deployment, dynos, add-ons, release management, scaling, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Heroku?","content":"Heroku is a cloud PaaS that abstracts infrastructure so developers can push apps with Git-based deployment and use dyno containers."},{"heading":"Why Heroku?","content":"It simplifies deployment, autoscaling, offers a rich add-on marketplace, and supports many languages and frameworks."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Install Heroku CLI, run `heroku login`, `git push heroku main` to deploy."},{"heading":"2. Dynos & Process Types","content":"Use dynos for web, worker, clock processes; scale dynos via CLI or dashboard."},{"heading":"3. Buildpacks","content":"Use official or custom buildpacks to compile and run apps across multiple languages."},{"heading":"4. Environment Config & Config Vars","content":"Manage config variables (`heroku config:set`) for secrets like API keys."},{"heading":"5. Add‑ons Marketplace","content":"Add services like Postgres, Redis, RabbitMQ, LogDNA directly to your app."},{"heading":"6. Databases & Backups","content":"Use Heroku Postgres, automate backups, and follow retention policies."},{"heading":"7. Logging & Monitoring","content":"Use `heroku logs --tail`, add-ons like Papertrail, New Relic, or built-in metrics."},{"heading":"8. Scaling & Dyno Types","content":"Scale horizontally by dyno count; use Performance dynos for high load."},{"heading":"9. Pipelines & Review Apps","content":"Set up pipelines for staging/production, auto-create review apps per PR."},{"heading":"10. CI Integration","content":"Use Heroku CI or connect with GitHub Actions for testing and deployments."},{"heading":"11. Deployment Methods","content":"Deploy via Git, GitHub integration, Docker, or CI pipelines."},{"heading":"12. SSL & Custom Domains","content":"Manage domains, auto‑provision SSL with Let’s Encrypt."},{"heading":"13. Worker & Background Jobs","content":"Use worker dynos for tasks using `heroku ps:scale worker=1`."},{"heading":"14. Jobs, Scheduler & Cron","content":"Use Heroku Scheduler or third-party add‑ons for scheduled jobs."},{"heading":"15. Review and Scratch orgs","content":"Use ephemeral review apps for testing PRs; destroy after use."},{"heading":"16. Performance Optimization","content":"Use concurrency, cache layers (Redis), build performance dynos."},{"heading":"17. Autoscaling","content":"Use autoscaling add-ons to automatically adjust dyno counts based on load."},{"heading":"18. Release Lifecycle","content":"Use `heroku releases`, rollback easily, manage rollback strategy."},{"heading":"19. Security & Compliance","content":"Rotate keys, enable private spaces/VPN, use Heroku shield for enterprise compliance."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Treat dynos as cattle (immutable)\n- Clean up unused add-ons\n- Use multi-tenant pipelines\n- Monitor metrics and set alerts"}],"related":["kotlin-roadmap","cpp-roadmap","contentful-roadmap","truffle-roadmap","mongodb-roadmap"]},{"slug":"digitalocean-roadmap","title":"DigitalOcean Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master DigitalOcean in 2025 with this roadmap covering droplets, networking, Kubernetes, storage, security, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is DigitalOcean?","content":"A cloud infrastructure provider offering straightforward compute, storage, and networking services built for simplicity and developer-friendliness."},{"heading":"Why DigitalOcean?","content":"It combines easy-to-use UI, predictable pricing, and powerful APIs—ideal for startups, hobby projects, and production workloads."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Sign up, verify, create your first project and droplet (choose OS, region, size)."},{"heading":"2. SSH & Secure Access","content":"Add SSH key, use SSH agent, disable password access, configure firewall."},{"heading":"3. Droplet Management","content":"Resize, snapshot, back-up, restore, use tags and projects."},{"heading":"4. Networking & Load Balancers","content":"Set up private networks, floating IPs, and load balancers with health checks."},{"heading":"5. DNS & Domains","content":"Manage domain records via DigitalOcean DNS with automatic LetsEncrypt provisioning."},{"heading":"6. Kubernetes (DOKS)","content":"Provision clusters, configure node pools, autoscaling, and deploy workloads."},{"heading":"7. Managed Databases","content":"Use managed PostgreSQL, MySQL, Redis—setup backups, high‑availability, and "},{"heading":"8. Block & Object Storage","content":"Use block storage volumes and Spaces for storage & CDN."},{"heading":"9. App Platform","content":"Deploy apps via source code repos with managed builds and auto-scaling."},{"heading":"10. Container Registry","content":"Use the private container registry for image storage and DOKS integration."},{"heading":"11. Serverless & Functions","content":"Use Functions project for event-driven functions."},{"heading":"12. Security & Firewalls","content":"Use cloud firewalls, DDoS protections, OAuth API tokens."},{"heading":"13. Monitoring & Alerts","content":"Enable monitoring, configure alerts for CPU/disk/memory usage."},{"heading":"14. Backups & Snapshots","content":"Schedule automatic backups and manage snapshots for disaster recovery."},{"heading":"15. CI/CD Workflows","content":"Integrate with GitHub, GitLab, or use Pipelines & registries."},{"heading":"16. Infrastructure as Code","content":"Use Terraform or Pulumi to define and manage infrastructure."},{"heading":"17. Datacenter & Region Strategy","content":"Use multi-region deployments and DR configurations."},{"heading":"18. Cost Management","content":"Use cost dashboards and cleanup unused resources."},{"heading":"19. High Availability","content":"Use multiple droplets / load balancers and managed DB HA."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep images updated\n- Automate backups & snapshots\n- Tag resources\n- Use IAM least privilege\n- Monitor usage continuously"}],"related":["pytorch-roadmap","supabase-roadmap","google-cloud-roadmap","metamask-roadmap","passportjs-roadmap"]},{"slug":"nginx-roadmap","title":"Nginx Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Nginx in 2025 with this roadmap covering web serving, reverse proxy, load balancing, security, and performance tuning.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Nginx?","content":"A high-performance HTTP server, reverse proxy, and mail proxy designed for performance, scalability, and reliability."},{"heading":"Why Nginx?","content":"Handles high concurrency workloads efficiently using asynchronous architecture; widely used in modern infrastructure."},{"heading":"1. Installation","content":"Install via package manager or compile from source; configure basic `nginx.conf`."},{"heading":"2. Basic Configuration","content":"Define `server`, `location`, directives, listen ports, server_name and root."},{"heading":"3. Reverse Proxy","content":"Use `proxy_pass` for upstream services, with headers (`X-Forwarded-For`) and health-checks."},{"heading":"4. Load Balancing","content":"Use `upstream` block, define round-robin, least_conn, IP-hash balancing."},{"heading":"5. SSL/TLS","content":"Implement HTTPS using certificates, support SNI, OCSP stapling, strong protocols."},{"heading":"6. Caching & Compression","content":"Use `proxy_cache`, `gzip`, `brotli` for performance optimization."},{"heading":"7. Security Hardening","content":"Control headers, limit rate, restrict requests, integrate with Fail2Ban/WAF."},{"heading":"8. URL Rewriting","content":"Use `rewrite`, redirects, error page handling."},{"heading":"9. Static File Serving","content":"Configure efficient static content delivery with `aio`, `sendfile`,expires headers."},{"heading":"10. WebSockets & HTTP/2","content":"Support WebSockets and enable HTTP/2 for multiplexing, performance."},{"heading":"11. Gzip & Brotli","content":"Enable compression of responses on-the-fly."},{"heading":"12. Access & Error Logging","content":"Configure log formats, rotate logs, parse using ELK stack."},{"heading":"13. Rate Limiting & Throttling","content":"Use `limit_req`, `limit_conn` directives per zone."},{"heading":"14. Virtual Hosts","content":"Host multiple domains with separate server blocks."},{"heading":"15. Monitoring","content":"Use stub_status module, integrate with Prometheus, Grafana."},{"heading":"16. Upgrades & Reload","content":"Use `systemctl reload` for zero-downtime. Test config with `nginx -t`."},{"heading":"17. Scripting with Lua","content":"Use `ngx_http_lua_module` for advanced request handling."},{"heading":"18. Accelerator & Streaming","content":"Stream large files efficiently with `buffering`, `chunked_transfer_encoding`."},{"heading":"19. Kubernetes Ingress","content":"Use NGINX Ingress Controller for clusters."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep config modular\n- Use minimal worker processes\n- Monitor resources\n- Automate certificate renewal\n- Use upstream health checks"}],"related":["mongodb-roadmap","redis-roadmap","chartjs-roadmap","webrtc-roadmap","jenkins-roadmap"]},{"slug":"apache-roadmap","title":"Apache HTTP Server Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Apache HTTP Server in 2025 with this roadmap covering installation, virtual hosts, security, performance tuning, modules, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Apache?","content":"Apache HTTP Server is a mature, open-source web server known for its modular architecture, cross-platform support, and widespread adoption."},{"heading":"Why Apache?","content":"It offers flexibility with modules, extensive configuration options, strong community support, and compatibility with legacy systems."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Install via package manager (apt, yum) or compile from source. Familiarize with `httpd.conf` and default directories."},{"heading":"2. Configuration Basics","content":"Understand directives like `ServerRoot`, `Listen`, `DocumentRoot`, and include structure in `.conf` files."},{"heading":"3. Virtual Hosts","content":"Host multiple sites using `<VirtualHost>` on IP or name-based configurations.","code":"<VirtualHost *:80>\n  ServerName example.com\n  DocumentRoot /var/www/example\n</VirtualHost>"},{"heading":"4. Modules & Extension","content":"Enable and configure modules like SSL, rewrite, proxy, headers; enable via `a2enmod` or `LoadModule` directives."},{"heading":"5. URL Rewriting & Redirection","content":"Use `mod_rewrite` for URL transforms, redirects, and SEO-friendly URLs.","code":"RewriteEngine On\nRewriteRule ^old-page$ /new-page [R=301,L]"},{"heading":"6. Authentication & Access Control","content":"Protect resources using `.htaccess`, basic auth, and role-based access with `mod_authz_core`."},{"heading":"7. TLS/SSL Configuration","content":"Set up HTTPS using `mod_ssl`, configure certificates, enable strong ciphers.","code":"<VirtualHost *:443>\n  SSLEngine on\n  SSLCertificateFile /path/cert.pem\n</VirtualHost>"},{"heading":"8. Performance Tuning","content":"Tune `KeepAlive`, `MaxRequestWorkers`, `EnableSendfile`, and `mod_cache` for speed."},{"heading":"9. Logging & Monitoring","content":"Configure `LogFormat`, `ErrorLog`, and integrate with monitoring tools like Prometheus or ELK stack."},{"heading":"10. Load Balancing & Proxy","content":"Use `mod_proxy`, `mod_proxy_balancer` for reverse proxying and distributing load."},{"heading":"11. Security Hardening","content":"Disable unused modules, limit allowed methods, add headers like `X-Frame-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`."},{"heading":"12. Content Compression","content":"Enable `mod_deflate` or `mod_brotli` for compressing responses."},{"heading":"13. HTTP/2 & HTTP/3","content":"Enable `mod_http2` and optionally QUIC support for next-gen protocols."},{"heading":"14. CGI & FastCGI","content":"Host dynamic apps via `mod_cgi`, `mod_fcgid`, or interface with PHP/FPM."},{"heading":"15. Embedded Web Apps","content":"Use `mod_wsgi`, `mod_perl` to run Python or Perl apps directly in Apache."},{"heading":"16. Clustering & High Availability","content":"Use in conjunction with HAProxy or keepalived for failover and scaling."},{"heading":"17. Automated Deployment","content":"Manage configs with Ansible, Chef, or Puppet and reload via `apachectl graceful`."},{"heading":"18. Testing & Validation","content":"Test config using `apachectl configtest` and validate SSL with SSL Labs."},{"heading":"19. Backup & Recovery","content":"Backup config files, certificates, and document root; plan disaster recovery."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use modular configs\n- Document changes via comments\n- Monitor resource usage\n- Keep Apache updated\n- Use HTTPS everywhere"}],"related":["typescript-roadmap","terraform-roadmap","aws-roadmap","kubernetes-roadmap","new-relic-roadmap"]},{"slug":"terraform-roadmap","title":"Terraform Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Terraform in 2025 with this roadmap covering infrastructure as code, state management, modules, cloud providers, CI/CD, and security best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Terraform?","content":"Terraform is a widely-used infrastructure-as-code tool by HashiCorp for provisioning, configuring, and managing cloud and on-prem resources declaratively."},{"heading":"Why Terraform?","content":"It enables reusable infrastructure code, supports multi-cloud, tracks infrastructure with state files, and integrates into CI/CD workflows."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Install via hashicorp releases or package manager; configure CLI and init workspaces."},{"heading":"2. HCL Syntax & Config Files","content":"Write `.tf` files using HCL, define `provider`, `resource`, `data`, and use `terraform fmt`/`validate`."},{"heading":"3. Variables & Outputs","content":"Parametrize configs using `variable`, `locals`, `output` blocks.","code":"variable \"region\" { type = string default = \"us-west-2\" }\noutput \"bucket_id\" { value = aws_s3_bucket.mybucket.id }"},{"heading":"4. Providers & Resources","content":"Configure providers (AWS, Azure, GCP) and define resources to create cloud infra."},{"heading":"5. State Management","content":"Understand local vs remote state, locking, backends (e.g., S3, GCS), and state drift issues."},{"heading":"6. Terraform Plan & Apply","content":"Use `terraform plan` to preview changes and `terraform apply` to execute infrastructure changes."},{"heading":"7. Modules & Reusability","content":"Organize code into reusable modules with input/output; use registry modules."},{"heading":"8. Workspaces & Environments","content":"Use workspaces or directory structures for multiple environments (dev, staging, prod)."},{"heading":"9. Provisioners & Null Resources","content":"Use provisioners (`local-exec`, `remote-exec`) sparingly for tasks like config management."},{"heading":"10. Data Sources","content":"Read existing infra values via `data` blocks for interdependent resources."},{"heading":"11. Dependency & Graph","content":"Terraform builds a dependency graph; use `depends_on` when implicit references are insufficient."},{"heading":"12. Secret & Credential Handling","content":"Secure sensitive variables using Terraform Cloud or Vault integrations."},{"heading":"13. Testing Infrastructure","content":"Use `terraform validate`, `tflint`, `terratest`, or `kitchen-terraform` for automated tests."},{"heading":"14. CI/CD Integration","content":"Integrate Terraform with pipelines (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI) with plan flows and approvals."},{"heading":"15. Drift Detection & State Recovery","content":"Use `terraform plan` to detect drift; use state commands for advanced state fixes."},{"heading":"16. Vault & External Data","content":"Integrate Vault for secrets and `external` data source for dynamic values."},{"heading":"17. Cloud Modules & Registry","content":"Use and publish modules from Terraform Registry for AWS, GCP, Azure, Kubernetes."},{"heading":"18. Scaling & Performance","content":"Split large configs, use CLI flags (`-parallelism`), and remote state."},{"heading":"19. Governance & Policy","content":"Use Sentinel or Open Policy Agent to enforce policies during planning."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep modules small and focused\n- Always review plans\n- Use remote state locking\n- Tag resources consistently\n- Keep providers up to date"}],"related":["netlify-roadmap","docker-roadmap","aspnet-roadmap","rails-roadmap","hasura-roadmap"]},{"slug":"ansible-roadmap","title":"Ansible Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Ansible in 2025 with this roadmap covering automation fundamentals, playbooks, inventories, modules, roles, and enterprise practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Ansible?","content":"Ansible is an agentless automation tool by Red Hat that uses SSH to configure systems, deploy apps, and orchestrate workflows via YAML playbooks."},{"heading":"Why Ansible?","content":"It enables reproducible infrastructure management, clear human-readable syntax, wide module support, and easy integration with CI/CD."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Install via pip or apt/yum (`pip install ansible`), verify with `ansible --version` and configure `ansible.cfg`."},{"heading":"2. Inventories & Hosts","content":"Define static (INI/YAML) or dynamic inventories. Test connectivity: `ansible all -m ping -i inventory`."},{"heading":"3. Simple Ad-hoc Commands","content":"Run quick tasks like `ansible all -m yum -a \"name=nginx state=present\"`."},{"heading":"4. Playbooks & Tasks","content":"Write YAML playbooks with `hosts`, `tasks`, `handlers`, `tags` and module usage."},{"heading":"5. Variables & Facts","content":"Use group_vars, host_vars, facts (`ansible_facts`), `set_fact`, defaults, and precedence."},{"heading":"6. Modules & Plugins","content":"Utilize built-in modules (`yum`, `template`, `uri`) and plugins (lookup, filter)."},{"heading":"7. Roles & File Structure","content":"Organize reusable logic under `roles/` with standard subfolders."},{"heading":"8. Handlers & Notify","content":"Use `handlers` to run actions conditionally, triggered via `notify`."},{"heading":"9. Conditionals & Loops","content":"Use `when`, `with_items`, `loop`, filters, and Jinja templating."},{"heading":"10. Templates with Jinja2","content":"Use `.j2` templates for dynamic configurations with variables and expressions."},{"heading":"11. Error Handling & Idempotence","content":"Enable `--check`, `--diff`, use `failed_when`, ensure safe retries."},{"heading":"12. Vault & Encryption","content":"Secure secrets with `ansible-vault`, use encrypted variables and files."},{"heading":"13. Dynamic Inventories","content":"Integrate with AWS, Azure, GCP, Kubernetes for auto hosts discovery."},{"heading":"14. Ansible Galaxy & Collections","content":"Use community roles with `ansible-galaxy`, create or publish Collections."},{"heading":"15. Testing & Linting","content":"Integrate `ansible-lint`, `yamllint`, and test with Molecule."},{"heading":"16. CI/CD Integration","content":"Plug into pipelines (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI) and run playbooks as steps."},{"heading":"17. Automation & Orchestration","content":"Use `ansible-pull`, orchestrate via Tower/AWX UI."},{"heading":"18. Performance Tuning","content":"Optimize control-machine, use pipelining, forks, delegate, throttle."},{"heading":"19. Enterprise & Tower","content":"Use Ansible Tower/AWX for RBAC, job scheduling, and credential management."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Keep roles small & focused\n- Use vault for secrets\n- Use CI & testing\n- Follow idempotence strictly"}],"related":["playwright-roadmap","elasticsearch-roadmap","digitalocean-roadmap","android-roadmap","algolia-roadmap"]},{"slug":"prometheus-roadmap","title":"Prometheus Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Prometheus in 2025 with this roadmap covering metrics collection, querying, alerting, exporting, and observability best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Prometheus?","content":"Prometheus is an open-source systems monitoring and alerting toolkit that collects real-time metrics via pull model and stores time-series data."},{"heading":"Why Prometheus?","content":"It offers powerful querying with PromQL, supports multi-dimensional data, and integrates with Grafana and Alertmanager for full observability."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Download Prometheus binary or use Docker, configure `prometheus.yml`, define scrape jobs."},{"heading":"2. Exposing Metrics","content":"Expose `/metrics` endpoints via client libraries (Go, Python, Node.js) or use exporters (node_exporter)."},{"heading":"3. Data Model & Labels","content":"Understand metric types (counter, gauge, histogram), naming conventions, and label organization."},{"heading":"4. PromQL Basics","content":"Write queries like `up`, `rate()`, `increase()`, learn functions and operators."},{"heading":"5. Recording Rules","content":"Define and store aggregated metrics for reuse and performance."},{"heading":"6. Service Discovery","content":"Automatically discover targets via Kubernetes, Consul, AWS, GCE."},{"heading":"7. Exporters & Integrations","content":"Use exporters: Node, Blackbox, MySQL, JMX; integrate with cloud and app instrumentation."},{"heading":"8. Alerting Rules","content":"Define alert expressions, durations and severity in `alert.rules.yml`."},{"heading":"9. Alertmanager Setup","content":"Configure routing, silences, receivers (email, Slack, PagerDuty)."},{"heading":"10. Grafana Integration","content":"Visualize Prometheus metrics with Grafana dashboards, templates, and alerts."},{"heading":"11. High Availability","content":"Set up Prometheus HA pairs and use remote_write to external long-term storage."},{"heading":"12. Long-Term Storage","content":"Integrate Thanos, Cortex, or Grafana Loki for durable metric storage."},{"heading":"13. Pushgateway Use Cases","content":"Use Pushgateway for batch jobs that push metrics."},{"heading":"14. Federation","content":"Scale metrics across clusters with federation."},{"heading":"15. Performance Tuning","content":"Tune scrape intervals, retention, storage TSDB, and memory."},{"heading":"16. Security & TLS","content":"Use TLS endpoints, authentication proxies, and secure scrape configs."},{"heading":"17. Automation & CI","content":"Generate scrape configs automatically and lint alerts in pipelines."},{"heading":"18. Multi-Tenancy Patterns","content":"Segment metrics by label or isolate via federation."},{"heading":"19. Troubleshooting & Debugging","content":"Use `/status`, UI for query troubleshooting, check targets, TSDB stats."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Use consistent metric naming\n- Keep labels minimal\n- Define alerts tuned to latency\n- Archive important data externally"}],"related":["bootstrap-roadmap","supabase-roadmap","kubernetes-roadmap","expressjs-roadmap","swift-roadmap"]},{"slug":"grafana-roadmap","title":"Grafana Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Grafana in 2025 with this roadmap covering visualization setup, data integrations, dashboards, alerting, and observability best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Grafana?","content":"Grafana is an open-source analytics & monitoring platform for querying, visualizing, alerting on, and exploring metrics across multiple data sources."},{"heading":"Why Grafana?","content":"It provides powerful, interactive dashboards, supports many data sources, alerting and annotations, and integrates seamlessly with Prometheus, ElasticSearch, Loki, and cloud services."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Install via Docker, binary or package (APT/YUM), then launch `grafana-server` and configure default admin credentials."},{"heading":"2. Data Source Integration","content":"Connect to Prometheus, Loki, MySQL, PostgreSQL, ElasticSearch, InfluxDB, AWS CloudWatch, etc."},{"heading":"3. Querying & Visualization","content":"Use Graph, Table, Gauge, and Heatmap panels; experiment with transformations and field overrides."},{"heading":"4. Dashboard Creation","content":"Organize metrics in rows & panels, use templating with variables (`${datasource}`) and folder structure."},{"heading":"5. Annotations & Events","content":"Add context to dashboards with automatic alert/event annotations."},{"heading":"6. Alerting & Notifications","content":"Configure alert rules per panel, set notification channels (Slack, email, PagerDuty).","code":"apiVersion: 1\nalert:\n  conditions:\n    - evaluator: \"gt(80)\"\n      query:\n        refId: A\nnotification:\n  - type: slack\n    uid: ops"},{"heading":"7. Provisioning & as Code","content":"Manage dashboards, datasources, alert rules via YAML/JSON provisioning files."},{"heading":"8. Plugin Ecosystem","content":"Enhance Grafana with community plugins: panels, datasources, apps and integrate custom plugins."},{"heading":"9. Sharing & Embedding","content":"Publish dashboards, snapshots, embed panels in applications via iframe or SDK scripts."},{"heading":"10. Authentication & RBAC","content":"Enable LDAP, OAuth and configure roles and permissions for users or organizations."},{"heading":"11. Scripting & Automation","content":"Use Grafana HTTP API or SDK for automation, provisioning, and CI pipelines."},{"heading":"12. Metrics and Logs Together","content":"Pair with Prometheus for metrics and Loki/Tempo for logs/traces for a complete observability stack."},{"heading":"13. Performance Optimization","content":"Use caching, optimize queries, limit time range, use dashboard variables to reduce load."},{"heading":"14. Team Collaboration","content":"Use folders, team permissions, dashboard versioning, and alerts to facilitate team workflows."},{"heading":"15. Grafana Cloud","content":"Explore hosted services, metrics storage (Mimir), and managed Tempo (tracing)."},{"heading":"16. Mobile & UX","content":"Use Grafana Mobile for on-call visibility, and optimize dashboards for small screens."},{"heading":"17. Licensing & Enterprise","content":"Understand the differences between OSS, Grafana Cloud Free, Pro, and Enterprise self-managed versions."},{"heading":"18. Security Best Practices","content":"Enable HTTPS, secure secrets, rotate API keys, restrict plugin source, set up IP allowlists."},{"heading":"19. Testing & Validation","content":"Use provisioning previews, automated UI checks in CI, use mock data sources for testing."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Modularize dashboards and alerts\n- Use version control for provisioning files\n- Monitor query performance\n- Limit heavy transformations client-side"}],"related":["cypress-roadmap","nodejs-roadmap","flutter-roadmap","aspnet-roadmap","ansible-roadmap"]},{"slug":"sentry-roadmap","title":"Sentry Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Sentry in 2025 with this roadmap covering error tracking, performance monitoring, integrations, alerting, and observability best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is Sentry?","content":"Sentry is an open-source crash/error reporting and performance monitoring platform that helps developers diagnose, triage, and fix issues across the software lifecycle."},{"heading":"Why Sentry?","content":"It captures detailed error and performance data, maps code paths, supports many platforms, and integrates deeply into development workflows."},{"heading":"1. Installation & SDK Setup","content":"Install via `npm install @sentry/node`, initialize in your app.","code":"Sentry.init({ dsn: __DSN__, tracesSampleRate: 1.0 });"},{"heading":"2. Error Reporting","content":"Automatically report exceptions and unhandled rejections, customize grouping & fingerprinting."},{"heading":"3. Performance Monitoring","content":"Capture spans and transactions to measure latency and throughput.","code":"const txn = Sentry.startTransaction({ name: 'GET /api' });\nSentry.getCurrentHub().configureScope(scope => scope.setSpan(txn));\n// ...end txn after response"},{"heading":"4. Breadcrumbs & Context","content":"Add user, tag, release context, custom breadcrumbs to enrich events."},{"heading":"5. Release Tracking & Source Maps","content":"Upload artifacts and sourcemaps for proper stack traces."},{"heading":"6. Alerts & Issue Workflows","content":"Configure alert rules, issue owners, and integrate with Slack, Jira, GitHub."},{"heading":"7. Issue Triage & Fingerprinting","content":"Customize grouping behavior and use fingerprinting to group or separate issues."},{"heading":"8. Inbound Filtering","content":"Use deny/allow lists, rate limits, and discard low-priority issues."},{"heading":"9. SDKs & Multi‑Language Support","content":"Use Sentry with JavaScript, Python, Java, Go, Ruby, mobile platforms, and frameworks."},{"heading":"10. Environment & Tag Usage","content":"Track separate environments (dev, staging, prod) and define contextual tags."},{"heading":"11. Performance Dashboard","content":"Monitor response times, throughput, ApDex, and hotspots."},{"heading":"12. Issue Group Management","content":"Use issue owners, suspect commits, alert escalation."},{"heading":"13. Enhanced Context","content":"Add Release, User, HTTP, UI, and Custom SDK context for rich debugging."},{"heading":"14. Tracing Distributed Systems","content":"Use performance and distributed tracing across microservices."},{"heading":"15. Source Code Integration","content":"Link Sentry with VCS for suspect commits and release management."},{"heading":"16. SDK Configuration","content":"Configure sample rates, attach stack trace data, control performance capture."},{"heading":"17. Testing & Validation","content":"Simulate errors and spans in test environments to validate tracing."},{"heading":"18. Privacy & GDPR","content":"Scrub PII, control data retention, deploy self-hosted Sentry for data compliance."},{"heading":"19. Scaling & Performance","content":"Use serverless Jetstream/LOS, sampling strategies, custom ingestion."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"- Set meaningful fingerprints\n- Use performance sampling cautiously\n- Tag events with context\n- Integrate into CI/CD and code reviews"}],"related":["linux-roadmap","unity-roadmap","sanity-io-roadmap","php-roadmap","python-roadmap"]},{"slug":"new-relic-roadmap","title":"New Relic Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master New Relic in 2025 with this roadmap covering platform setup, APM, AI monitoring, logs, dashboards, alerting, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is New Relic?","content":"New Relic is an enterprise-grade observability platform that provides holistic insights into applications, infrastructure, logs, events, and now AI workloads."},{"heading":"Why New Relic?","content":"It unifies telemetry—metrics, logs, traces—across the stack, supports automated AI content inspection and alerting, and integrates with CI/CD and collaboration tools."},{"heading":"1. Installation & Setup","content":"Install agents for APM (Java, Node.js, Python, .NET), infrastructure, browser, and mobile. Configure API keys and license."},{"heading":"2. APM & Infrastructure Monitoring","content":"Monitor transactions, service maps, traces, database queries, and integrate with Kubernetes or serverless environments."},{"heading":"3. New Relic Logs & Events","content":"Centralize logs, add custom attributes, query via NRQL, visualize alongside metrics and traces."},{"heading":"4. Dashboards & Visualizations","content":"Use dashboards built with charts, tables, and widgets; embed logs/traces; enable dynamic filters."},{"heading":"5. Alerting & Incident Response","content":"Create NRQL-based alerts, define thresholds and incident workflows, integrate with Slack/PagerDuty."},{"heading":"6. AI Monitoring","content":"Leverage industry’s first APM for AI—trace LLM performance, token usage, errors, latency, bias, cost across AI models and prompts."},{"heading":"7. Agentic AI Integrations","content":"Automate observability-enhanced workflows using ServiceNow and Gemini integrations to avoid context switching."},{"heading":"8. Predictive Analytics","content":"Forecast metrics (with ML) and use causal AI to explain anomalies; integrate predictions as alert conditions."},{"heading":"9. Transaction 360","content":"Use this feature for end-to-end service correlation and faster root-cause analysis across distributed systems."},{"heading":"10. Database Performance Monitoring","content":"Monitor query-level performance and execution plans for MySQL, PostgreSQL and SQL Server to uncover bottlenecks."},{"heading":"11. Queues & Streams","content":"Monitor Kafka, SQS, RabbitMQ with full producer/consumer visibility and topic-level insights."},{"heading":"12. CI/CD & CodeStream","content":"Integrate with pipelines and use CodeStream to view code-level metrics alongside production telemetry."},{"heading":"13. Security & Vulnerability Management","content":"Monitor open-source dependencies, detect vulnerabilities, and enforce compliance policies."},{"heading":"14. Observability Extensibility","content":"Capture custom data via Event API, create dashboards and query via NRQL."},{"heading":"15. Platform Automation","content":"Automate dashboards & alerts via YAML/JSON provisioning or CLI scripts."},{"heading":"16. Performance & Scalability","content":"Use data streaming, cache strategies, and intelligent sampling to manage volume and control costs."},{"heading":"17. High Availability & Multi‑Region","content":"Use HA setups, edge data routing, and redundant collectors."},{"heading":"18. Team & Access Management","content":"Define role-based access, SSO, team-level dashboard control, and audit logging."},{"heading":"19. Monitoring Ecosystem & Integrations","content":"Integrates with AWS, GCP, Azure, Kubernetes, GitHub Copilot, Gemini, and more."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"Deploy agents broadly, leverage AI tools (Predictions, Monitoring), optimize alert thresholds, and run regular telemetry reviews."}],"links":[{"text":"New Relic documentation","href":"https://docs.newrelic.com"},{"text":"New Relic AI Monitoring","href":"https://docs.newrelic.com/ai-monitoring"}],"related":["svelte-roadmap","apache-roadmap","php-roadmap","mongodb-roadmap","azure-roadmap"]},{"slug":"openai-api-roadmap","title":"OpenAI API Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master the OpenAI API in 2025 with this roadmap covering core models, chat completions, tool-augmented agent flows, webhooks, and advanced features.","sections":[{"heading":"What is OpenAI API?","content":"A unified API that provides access to powerful LLMs (GPT‑3.5, GPT‑4, GPT‑4o), embeddings, speech-to-text, and images for developers."},{"heading":"Why the OpenAI API?","content":"High-performance, multimodal models, integrated tool use, low-latency, usage analytics, and active roadmap courtesy of OpenAI."},{"heading":"1. Getting Started","content":"Sign-up, obtain your API key, install the SDK (`openai`), and test a completion request."},{"heading":"2. Models & Versions","content":"Use GPT‑3.5 Turbo (chat), GPT‑4, GPT‑4o (multimodal). OpenAI shifts to GPT‑5/4o2 pipeline."},{"heading":"3. Chat Completions API","content":"Build conversation histories with `messages` (system/user/assistant) and control via `temperature` and `max_tokens`."},{"heading":"4. Function Calling & Tools","content":"Define function schemas; let model invoke them and integrate tool usage in pipelines."},{"heading":"5. Embeddings API","content":"Generate semantic vectors for search, clustering, similarity matching."},{"heading":"6. Speech-to-Text & Audio","content":"Transcribe voice with Whisper models; support multi-language transcription."},{"heading":"7. Images API","content":"Generate and edit images using DALL·E endpoints."},{"heading":"8. Tooling & Webhooks","content":"Use webhooks for completions, fine-tuning, and retrieval events to build reactive systems."},{"heading":"9. Deep Research","content":"Use new Deep Research capabilities for multi-step question answering and agentic research workflows."},{"heading":"10. Plugins & Ecosystem","content":"Leverage community plugins, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), and search agent integrations."},{"heading":"11. Streaming & Latency Control","content":"Use `stream: true` to get partial tokens; manage latency with `chunks`."},{"heading":"12. Rate Limits & Usage Management","content":"Manage usage via quotas, handle `429` errors, backoff policies."},{"heading":"13. Fine-tuning & Embedding Specialization","content":"Customize base models with instruction tuning or RAG indexing."},{"heading":"14. Pricing Considerations","content":"Balance cost-quality tradeoff between GPT‑3.5, GPT‑4, GPT‑4o, fine-tuned, and tool-enabled models."},{"heading":"15. Security & Data Governance","content":"Use org policy, request redaction, avoid logging PII, apply network policies."},{"heading":"16. SDKs & Framework Integrations","content":"Use official SDKs (Node, Python), LangChain, LlamaIndex, and other orchestrators."},{"heading":"17. Testing & Monitoring","content":"Unit test prompts, evaluate hallucination rates, monitor via New Relic."},{"heading":"18. Multimodal Workflows","content":"Use GPT‑4o for vision + text pipelines: OCR, image understanding, captioning."},{"heading":"19. Next-gen: GPT‑5 & Multi-agent","content":"Transition to GPT‑5 line and use new protocols like Deep Research & Webhook support β released in June 2025."},{"heading":"20. Best Practices","content":"Prompt engineer with clear instructions, use functions, test edge cases, monitor usage and costs, and version prompt set."}],"links":[{"text":"OpenAI API Reference","href":"https://platform.openai.com/docs"},{"text":"June 2025 update: Deep Research & Webhooks","href":"https://sdtimes.com/ai/june-2025-all-ai-updates-from-the-past-month"}],"related":["huggingface-roadmap","playwright-roadmap","flutter-roadmap","google-cloud-roadmap","python-roadmap"]},{"slug":"langchain-roadmap","title":"LangChain Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master LangChain in 2025 with this roadmap covering agent orchestration, production deployment, LangGraph, LangSmith, and best practices.","sections":[{"heading":"What is LangChain?","content":"LangChain is a robust framework for developing LLM-powered applications, focusing on chains, agents, memory, and observability."},{"heading":"Why LangChain?","content":"It has evolved from rapid prototyping to production-grade integration hub, surpassing SDKs like OpenAI in usage and enabling enterprise-scale AI agent development"},{"heading":"1. Core & Model Support","content":"Support for GPT‑5, LLaMA‑4, Gemini 2 Ultra, Mistral, Claude 4, plus connectors for enterprise systems (SAP, Salesforce, ServiceNow)"},{"heading":"2. Agent Orchestration (LangGraph)","content":"LangGraph 1.0 GA enables multi-agent orchestration, node-level caching, interrupts, deferred nodes, with secure FastAPI + LangGraph templates"},{"heading":"3. LangSmith & Obser