slug":"webrtc-roadmap","title":"WebRTC Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master WebRTC in 2025 with this roadmap covering core APIs, security, emerging protocols, AI integration, and best practices for real-time web communication.","sections":[{"heading":"What is WebRTC?","content":"WebRTC is a browser-native technology that enables real-time peer-to-peer audio, video, and data communication without plugins."},{"heading":"Why WebRTC?","content":"Popular for video conferencing, live-streaming, VoIP, and real-time apps because it's plugin-free, secure (DTLS‑SRTP), and supported by all major browsers."},{"heading":"1. RTCRtpScriptTransform","content":"Script-based transforms on RTP streams enabling custom processing (like E2EE). A focus of Interop 2025 efforts."},{"heading":"2. Transferable RTCDataChannels","content":"Support for transferring data channels to Web Workers for off-main-thread processing, improving performance."},{"heading":"3. WHIP & WHEP Protocols","content":"HTTP-based ingress (WHIP) and egress (WHEP) streaming protocols gaining adoption for easier media workflows."},{"heading":"4. Media over QUIC / HTTP/3","content":"Streaming over QUIC/HTTP3 is under draft to improve latency, reliability, and reduce head-of-line blocking."},{"heading":"5. WebCodecs & WebGPU","content":"Low-level media encoding/decoding and GPU-based processing (via WebGPU) for high-performance tasks."},{"heading":"6. WebXR Integration","content":"Better AR/VR support through WebRTC-powered immersive experiences."},{"heading":"7. WebUSB/WebBluetooth for Device Access","content":"Support to interface with external media devices in real-time communications."},{"heading":"8. AI & ML in Audio/Video","content":"Emerging usage of AI for real-time transcription, translation, noise suppression, video editing, and sentiment analysis."},{"heading":"9. Standards & Interop","content":"Ongoing standardization via W3C (e.g., media capture / stream, statistics), with interoperability testing underway :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}."},{"heading":"10. Enterprise & 5G Edge","content":"Integration into telehealth, contact centers, 5G networks, with edge computing for low-latency use cases :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}."},{"heading":"11. Best Practices","content":"- Use DTLS‑SRTP encryption\n- Leverage WHIP/WHEP for simplified pipelines\n- Design for transferable channels/workers\n- Integrate AI for improved UX\n- Monitor via telemetry for performance and security"}],"links":[{"text":"W3C WebRTC Working Group Charter","href":"https://www.w3.org/2024/08/webrtc-charter.html"},{"text":"What’s Next for WebRTC in 2025","href":"https://webrtc.ventures/2025/01/whats-next-for-webrtc-in-2025/"}],"related":["vue-roadmap","linux-roadmap","react-roadmap","playwright-roadmap","jenkins-roadmap"]},{"slug":"storybook-roadmap","title":"Storybook Roadmap: A Complete Guide [2025 Updated]","description":"Master Storybook in 2025 with this roadmap covering new release cadence, accessibility, component testing, ecosystem integration, and upcoming improvements.","sections":[{"heading":"Summary of Roadmap","content":"Storybook maintains an active public roadmap on GitHub, releasing minor versions every ~8 weeks and majors annually (usually Feb/Mar) :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}."},{"heading":"1. Recent Release – Storybook 8.5","content":"Introduced Realtime a11y testing via Axe, project-level code coverage, focused component tests, React Native Web Vite support, and Test Bootcamp :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}."},{"heading":"2. Test & Accessibility Integration","content":"Built-in component tests with Vitest, Axe-based accessibility linting, and coverage reports."},{"heading":"3. Framework API & Builder Upgrades","content":"Framework API supports zero-config across Vite, Next.js, SvelteKit, Remix, Nuxt; Vite builder prioritized, Turbopack integration in progress :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}."},{"heading":"4. React Native, Svelt